WEBVTT

1
00:00:44.908 --> 00:00:46.909
[CHATTERING ON TV]

2
00:01:30.871 --> 00:01:32.121
[DOOR CLOSES]

3
00:01:36.168 --> 00:01:37.919
Okay.

4
00:01:46.970 --> 00:01:48.888
You all right?

5
00:01:49.807 --> 00:01:51.432
Yeah.

6
00:01:57.022 --> 00:02:00.900
You'd think these trips would
get easier. but it's just the opposite.

7
00:02:01.527 --> 00:02:04.362
Well. I feel the same way. Ange.

8
00:02:06.740 --> 00:02:09.784
ANDREA:
I know this is what we do.
This is our life.

9
00:02:09.952 --> 00:02:13.621
But it just seems like the world
is moving so fast.

10
00:02:14.915 --> 00:02:18.543
and right now
things are changing so much.

11
00:02:20.754 --> 00:02:22.630
They sure are.

12
00:02:24.091 --> 00:02:28.010
I'll tell you something.
It's not gonna be easy for our kids.

13
00:02:28.220 --> 00:02:31.889
They're going into a different world
than the one you and I came into.

14
00:02:32.099 --> 00:02:33.558
Yeah.

15
00:02:33.767 --> 00:02:36.936
You know.
both our kids are doing great.

16
00:02:37.145 --> 00:02:40.940
But it worries me when Danny
doesn't take school seriously.

17
00:02:41.149 --> 00:02:44.485
Him missing class.
That could come out...

18
00:02:44.653 --> 00:02:48.030
It might hurt him when he's out
looking for a job. you know?

19
00:02:48.198 --> 00:02:51.075
The competition out there.
When I was starting out.

20
00:02:51.243 --> 00:02:54.912
you could make captain if you put
your head down and did your work.

21
00:02:55.080 --> 00:02:56.789
But young guys coming up now...

22
00:02:56.999 --> 00:02:59.125
Companies want things faster
and cheaper.

23
00:02:59.293 --> 00:03:02.044
And 50 guys compete for every job.

24
00:03:02.796 --> 00:03:05.590
Everything's different.
and big wheels are turning.

25
00:03:05.757 --> 00:03:07.967
You gotta be strong
to survive out there.

26
00:03:08.385 --> 00:03:09.677
Mm.

27
00:03:11.305 --> 00:03:13.431
I hear what you're saying.

28
00:03:13.599 --> 00:03:15.892
It's gonna be okay. right?

29
00:03:16.059 --> 00:03:17.101
Oh. yeah.

30
00:03:20.188 --> 00:03:21.689
Gonna be okay.

31
00:03:32.826 --> 00:03:34.952
MAN [OVER PA]:
This is a special
security announcement.

32
00:03:35.120 --> 00:03:38.497
Please maintain control
of your personal belongings at all times.

33
00:03:38.665 --> 00:03:44.211
Unattended baggage is subject
to search. inspection and removal.

34
00:03:47.925 --> 00:03:49.675
I love you.
Love you too.

35
00:03:51.053 --> 00:03:54.055
Have a safe trip.
I'll call you from there.

36
00:04:05.567 --> 00:04:07.568
[CHATTERING IN SOMALI]

37
00:04:14.034 --> 00:04:16.869
[BASS THUMPING OVER SPEAKERS]

38
00:04:17.287 --> 00:04:18.871
[PEOPLE CLAMORING]

39
00:04:33.887 --> 00:04:35.888
[BOY SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

40
00:04:36.890 --> 00:04:38.057
[IN SOMALI]
They're here!

41
00:04:39.434 --> 00:04:40.851
Hurry. Muse!

42
00:04:59.788 --> 00:05:02.957
MAN [IN SOMALI]:
What the hell are you doing?
Why aren't you out on the water?

43
00:05:03.125 --> 00:05:05.960
You know what you're supposed to do!

44
00:05:07.462 --> 00:05:11.132
You should be out there
earning money!

45
00:05:11.299 --> 00:05:13.843
[IN SOMALI]
But we caught a ship last week.

46
00:05:14.011 --> 00:05:15.970
That was last week!

47
00:05:16.430 --> 00:05:18.556
The boss wants money today!

48
00:05:18.724 --> 00:05:21.267
Bring Garaad another ship soon

49
00:05:21.435 --> 00:05:23.144
or you will answer for it!

50
00:05:23.311 --> 00:05:24.311
[GUNSHOTS]

51
00:05:24.479 --> 00:05:26.647
Everybody. get back
to work now!

52
00:05:26.857 --> 00:05:28.816
[CHATTERING]

53
00:05:36.408 --> 00:05:38.909
[IN SOMALI]
Stay out of my way today.

54
00:05:41.288 --> 00:05:43.789
ASAD [IN SOMALI]:
Hufan!

55
00:05:43.957 --> 00:05:47.043
I'm going to get us something big!

56
00:05:47.836 --> 00:05:51.088
HUFAN:
Those who want to make money.
come.

57
00:05:51.590 --> 00:05:54.467
[IN SOMALI]
Muse. take me with you.

58
00:05:54.634 --> 00:05:56.510
[IN SOMALI]
Does your sister know
you're here?

59
00:05:56.678 --> 00:05:58.971
She's selling khat up there.

60
00:05:59.139 --> 00:06:02.016
This is her best stuff.

61
00:06:03.060 --> 00:06:04.894
[BOTH SPEAKING IN SOMALI]

62
00:06:05.062 --> 00:06:07.063
[MEN CLAMORING]

63
00:06:07.230 --> 00:06:09.231
[ASAD SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

64
00:06:10.108 --> 00:06:13.027
ASAD:
When we get a big ship.
you will be well paid.

65
00:06:13.612 --> 00:06:14.904
You want to work?

66
00:06:15.072 --> 00:06:17.198
Do you know how to steer a boat?

67
00:06:17.365 --> 00:06:19.575
Go. go.

68
00:06:19.785 --> 00:06:21.243
[IN SOMALI]
I'm ready.

69
00:06:21.411 --> 00:06:23.079
What do you have for me?
Money.

70
00:06:23.246 --> 00:06:26.499
When are you gonna give it to me?
As soon as we're paid.

71
00:06:27.292 --> 00:06:30.127
HUFAN:
Spread out!

72
00:06:30.921 --> 00:06:34.757
Let my other man choose his crew.

73
00:06:35.592 --> 00:06:38.719
ASAD:
Next time bring me something
if you want to work.

74
00:06:38.929 --> 00:06:40.471
[MEN CLAMORING]

75
00:06:50.941 --> 00:06:52.733
MUSE:
Come on. Bilal.

76
00:06:55.028 --> 00:06:58.364
[IN SOMALI]
Hey. Skinny. I can steer your boat.

77
00:06:58.532 --> 00:07:00.658
If you choose me. you won't regret it.

78
00:07:03.703 --> 00:07:04.954
Okay. Elmi.

79
00:07:05.163 --> 00:07:07.164
[MEN CLAMORING]

80
00:07:08.333 --> 00:07:11.043
I need somebody strong.

81
00:07:12.879 --> 00:07:15.172
Somebody like this?

82
00:07:25.433 --> 00:07:27.309
I want him.

83
00:07:27.477 --> 00:07:30.146
[IN SOMALI]
Get out of my way!

84
00:07:33.191 --> 00:07:35.067
[IN SOMALI]
Why did he pick him?

85
00:07:35.235 --> 00:07:37.486
He's from another village.

86
00:07:38.363 --> 00:07:40.364
[CHATTERING]

87
00:07:40.574 --> 00:07:42.575
[♪♪♪]

88
00:07:57.507 --> 00:07:59.508
[SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

89
00:08:27.454 --> 00:08:28.954
ASAD:
Move!

90
00:08:29.122 --> 00:08:32.082
Faster. move faster!

91
00:08:36.755 --> 00:08:38.172
[CHATTERING]

92
00:08:41.509 --> 00:08:43.093
See if you can get more power.

93
00:08:44.971 --> 00:08:46.263
Okay.

94
00:08:46.431 --> 00:08:47.973
ASAD:
You!

95
00:08:49.267 --> 00:08:51.644
Get over here!

96
00:08:51.811 --> 00:08:53.604
Come help us!

97
00:08:56.149 --> 00:08:58.150
[♪♪♪]

98
00:09:21.258 --> 00:09:23.259
[MIDDLE-EASTERN MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

99
00:09:46.533 --> 00:09:48.534
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER PA]

100
00:09:56.835 --> 00:09:59.628
WORKER:
Okay. pull it in!

101
00:09:59.796 --> 00:10:01.130
Sign right there. sir.

102
00:10:01.339 --> 00:10:02.840
You have a good day.

103
00:10:03.049 --> 00:10:05.926
Hello. Cap. Let me get that for you.
Morning.

104
00:10:57.771 --> 00:11:00.189
MAN 1 [OVER PA]:
Attention. all crew. All crew.

105
00:11:00.398 --> 00:11:03.150
1500 departure three out.

106
00:11:10.617 --> 00:11:13.744
Hey. good to see you. Cap.
Shane. Good to see you.

107
00:11:13.912 --> 00:11:16.413
Good to see you.
Hey. Carry on.

108
00:11:16.581 --> 00:11:17.873
SHANE: Hey. bos?
MAN 2: Yeah?

109
00:11:18.083 --> 00:11:19.958
SHANE:
Get on that safety rail. huh?

110
00:11:20.168 --> 00:11:21.335
Kenny.
KENNY: Yeah?

111
00:11:21.544 --> 00:11:25.339
I want you to go down to the deck office.
grab Jimmy. get on the Lodestar.

112
00:11:25.507 --> 00:11:29.551
Mm-hm.
That ballast. move it five points.

113
00:11:29.719 --> 00:11:31.762
Take care of that now.
You got it.

114
00:11:32.305 --> 00:11:34.264
SHANE:
How's the family. Cap?

115
00:11:34.432 --> 00:11:36.225
Oh. you know.

116
00:11:36.393 --> 00:11:40.229
Andrea's a champ. one kid gone.
another kid going.

117
00:11:40.397 --> 00:11:41.647
How are the boxes?

118
00:11:41.815 --> 00:11:44.900
SHANE:
Oh. you know.
Just putting a few last containers on.

119
00:11:45.110 --> 00:11:49.238
Twenty-four hundred tons of
commercial cargo. 200 tons of food aid.

120
00:11:49.447 --> 00:11:54.535
166 tons of freshwater.
250 metric tons of fuel bunkered.

121
00:11:54.702 --> 00:11:57.037
PHILLIPS:
Walk me through the plan.

122
00:11:59.874 --> 00:12:01.333
So here we are in Salalah.

123
00:12:02.544 --> 00:12:05.546
Travel down the coalition corridor
to Djibouti.

124
00:12:05.713 --> 00:12:07.005
Then we exit the shipping lane

125
00:12:07.173 --> 00:12:09.133
south of Socotra.

126
00:12:09.300 --> 00:12:11.051
Socotra. okay.

127
00:12:11.219 --> 00:12:15.639
SHANE:
Then we're on our own down the coast
through the Somali Basin.

128
00:12:15.849 --> 00:12:17.933
all the way down to Mombasa.

129
00:12:18.101 --> 00:12:20.227
MAN 1 [OVER RADIO]:
We need five minutes
on that reefer bow.

130
00:12:23.356 --> 00:12:26.942
We should be able
to unload the containers around 0800.

131
00:12:27.944 --> 00:12:31.196
Well. let's tighten up security.

132
00:12:31.364 --> 00:12:34.199
We are going
around the Horn of Africa. right?

133
00:12:34.367 --> 00:12:38.454
We got pirate cages. They were
all open. All the doors are unlocked.

134
00:12:38.621 --> 00:12:41.290
I want everything closed. locked.
even in port.

135
00:12:42.500 --> 00:12:46.003
Right.
Fine. Ready to leave. 1500.

136
00:12:46.171 --> 00:12:48.213
Absolutely. Cap. You got it.

137
00:12:48.423 --> 00:12:50.424
[♪♪♪]

138
00:12:54.721 --> 00:12:57.139
Stow the gangway.

139
00:12:57.307 --> 00:12:58.515
Last lines in.

140
00:13:00.810 --> 00:13:01.935
Okay. Lower it.

141
00:13:02.103 --> 00:13:05.397
WORKER 1:
Sixteen-B ready. Take it up.

142
00:13:06.608 --> 00:13:07.691
WORKER 2:
Tighten it up.

143
00:13:07.859 --> 00:13:09.860
Hey. slow down.

144
00:13:13.448 --> 00:13:14.948
Bow clear.

145
00:13:15.116 --> 00:13:16.325
WORKER 3:
Stern lines are clear.

146
00:13:16.534 --> 00:13:18.243
Bow thruster full starboard.

147
00:13:19.537 --> 00:13:21.830
SHANE:
Bow thruster on.

148
00:13:28.087 --> 00:13:30.339
WORKER 4:
All lines clear. Ship is under way.

149
00:13:32.008 --> 00:13:34.218
Dead slow ahead.
Dead slow ahead.

150
00:13:34.427 --> 00:13:36.428
[♪♪♪]

151
00:14:30.066 --> 00:14:32.025
MAN 1:
Keep those hatches locked down.

152
00:14:32.235 --> 00:14:33.485
MAN 2: Cap.
Morning.

153
00:14:47.208 --> 00:14:49.167
MAN 3:
Check that rigging.

154
00:14:57.802 --> 00:14:59.803
[MEN CHATTERING]

155
00:15:02.432 --> 00:15:04.266
PHILLIPS: Shane.
SHANE: Yeah?

156
00:15:04.434 --> 00:15:05.892
We need those time sheets.

157
00:15:06.102 --> 00:15:09.104
She's winking at me.
But it turns out that's what they do.

158
00:15:09.314 --> 00:15:11.607
I'll show you this place. I'll take you.

159
00:15:11.774 --> 00:15:13.900
I'll have two beers
and a bucketful of sin. please.

160
00:15:14.068 --> 00:15:15.861
[MEN LAUGHING]

161
00:15:16.029 --> 00:15:18.655
Yeah. About done with that coffee?

162
00:15:20.491 --> 00:15:22.242
Yeah.
CRONAN: Yeah. we're done.

163
00:15:22.869 --> 00:15:24.494
SHANE:
That's 15. guys.

164
00:15:25.121 --> 00:15:26.997
Back to work. Come on. let's go.

165
00:15:27.165 --> 00:15:30.042
Jesus.
MAN: See you down there. Mike.

166
00:15:38.259 --> 00:15:40.260
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

167
00:15:45.808 --> 00:15:49.019
HUFAN:
Their main route is packed
with ships

168
00:15:50.563 --> 00:15:53.190
but we can't attack a herd.

169
00:15:59.656 --> 00:16:02.741
This one is alone.

170
00:16:18.174 --> 00:16:20.384
[ERIC CLAPTON'S
"WONDERFUL TONIGHT"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

171
00:16:20.551 --> 00:16:22.094
♪ She puts on her makeup ♪

172
00:16:24.681 --> 00:16:28.350
♪ And brushes her long blonde hair ♪

173
00:16:29.769 --> 00:16:37.192
♪ And then she asks me.
"Do I look all right?" ♪

174
00:16:37.360 --> 00:16:45.033
♪ And I say.
"Yes. you look wonderful tonight ♪♪

175
00:16:46.119 --> 00:16:47.577
[SIGHS]

176
00:17:00.675 --> 00:17:02.426
Morning.

177
00:17:03.010 --> 00:17:04.177
Hey. Cap.

178
00:17:04.345 --> 00:17:05.929
KENNY: Cap.
Morning. Cap.

179
00:17:06.097 --> 00:17:09.808
Shane. I want to do some security drills.
unannounced.

180
00:17:09.976 --> 00:17:11.476
Starting now.

181
00:17:11.644 --> 00:17:14.062
Uh. what? Fire. man overboard?

182
00:17:14.230 --> 00:17:16.815
Everything.
Ken. you're the duty officer?

183
00:17:16.983 --> 00:17:18.442
Yeah. Cap.
Right.

184
00:17:18.609 --> 00:17:22.154
Boat with two armed men is approaching
on your starboard beam.

185
00:17:23.364 --> 00:17:25.031
No. no. Whistle first.
SHANE: Let's go.

186
00:17:25.199 --> 00:17:26.491
[HORN BLARES]

187
00:17:26.659 --> 00:17:29.786
That way the pirates
know we're aware of them
and are ready to defend the ship.

188
00:17:30.580 --> 00:17:31.663
Hustle up. Let's go.

189
00:17:31.831 --> 00:17:33.707
[SIREN WAILING]

190
00:17:33.875 --> 00:17:35.208
Attention. all crew.

191
00:17:35.376 --> 00:17:38.587
[OVER PA] All crew.
All men to your stations on deck.

192
00:17:38.755 --> 00:17:42.340
Repeat.
all men to your deck stations now.

193
00:17:42.550 --> 00:17:44.384
Let's do this.

194
00:17:44.844 --> 00:17:46.845
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

195
00:17:49.599 --> 00:17:53.769
Come on... Get those keys off your hip.
Put them in your pocket. Come on. guys.

196
00:17:53.936 --> 00:17:56.104
Pirates capture you
and find those keys.

197
00:17:56.272 --> 00:17:58.857
they'll have access to every door
on this ship.

198
00:18:05.948 --> 00:18:08.575
MAN 1:
Get those hoses on.

199
00:18:08.743 --> 00:18:11.453
Bring it around. bring around.
bring around.

200
00:18:11.621 --> 00:18:14.372
MAN 2: Watch it. man.
MAN 1: Ready with number six.

201
00:18:14.540 --> 00:18:15.665
SHANE:
All right.

202
00:18:16.334 --> 00:18:17.417
You tied up?

203
00:18:18.044 --> 00:18:20.128
MAN 3:
All done here. Shane.

204
00:18:20.963 --> 00:18:24.382
Hey. Cap. this is Shane. Do you read?
Yeah. Shane. go ahead.

205
00:18:24.550 --> 00:18:28.220
Things are looking good down here.
We're getting close with the hoses.

206
00:18:28.721 --> 00:18:31.431
All right. Let me know
when you're ready down there.

207
00:18:31.599 --> 00:18:33.058
Copy that.

208
00:18:34.977 --> 00:18:37.646
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

209
00:18:39.190 --> 00:18:41.191
[BEEPING]

210
00:18:48.324 --> 00:18:50.325
[♪♪♪]

211
00:18:52.078 --> 00:18:54.579
Shane. come up to the bridge.

212
00:18:54.789 --> 00:18:56.706
SHANE:
Okay.

213
00:19:12.265 --> 00:19:14.266
[♪♪♪]

214
00:19:16.102 --> 00:19:18.770
What's up. Cap? Everything okay?

215
00:19:18.938 --> 00:19:21.147
I don't like the look of that.

216
00:19:28.072 --> 00:19:29.447
[DIALING]

217
00:19:30.867 --> 00:19:33.577
Yeah. Cap.
Chief. I want all your guys on station.

218
00:19:34.537 --> 00:19:35.579
Still in the drill?

219
00:19:35.746 --> 00:19:39.040
This is real-world. Someone coming up
on our starboard quarter.

220
00:19:39.208 --> 00:19:40.917
Got it.

221
00:19:41.127 --> 00:19:43.128
[♪♪♪]

222
00:19:43.713 --> 00:19:46.631
Port. 5 degrees.
Let's see if they follow us.

223
00:19:46.799 --> 00:19:47.841
Port. 5.

224
00:19:56.475 --> 00:19:58.476
[♪♪♪]

225
00:19:59.687 --> 00:20:02.689
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

226
00:20:05.985 --> 00:20:08.403
Get the crew back
to their muster stations.

227
00:20:08.613 --> 00:20:10.071
Right.

228
00:20:10.573 --> 00:20:13.575
Attention. all crew.
Return to your muster stations.

229
00:20:13.743 --> 00:20:16.745
[OVER PA]
Repeat. return to your muster stations.

230
00:20:16.913 --> 00:20:20.624
This is not a drill.
This is a real-world situation.

231
00:20:21.709 --> 00:20:24.836
Yeah. Cap.
I want to come up to 122.

232
00:20:25.004 --> 00:20:27.255
Second mate and helmsman
to the bridge.

233
00:20:29.133 --> 00:20:30.842
You're good. Bring her on up.

234
00:20:31.052 --> 00:20:32.427
[♪♪♪]

235
00:20:42.146 --> 00:20:44.856
Now get me U.S. Maritime Emergency.

236
00:20:46.484 --> 00:20:48.068
[DIALING]

237
00:20:52.949 --> 00:20:55.492
Two skiffs.
Can't tell how many they're carrying.

238
00:20:55.701 --> 00:20:56.743
SHANE:
Copy that.

239
00:20:56.911 --> 00:20:59.788
There's no answer
at the U.S. Maritime Emergency line.

240
00:20:59.956 --> 00:21:02.165
Raise the UKMTO.
Right.

241
00:21:02.333 --> 00:21:03.458
What's up?

242
00:21:03.626 --> 00:21:06.378
We got two skiffs approaching.
Get on the radar.

243
00:21:10.925 --> 00:21:14.427
Yeah. this is the Maersk Alabama.
Here's the captain.

244
00:21:15.221 --> 00:21:16.471
UKMTO.

245
00:21:17.640 --> 00:21:19.391
Operations?
WOMAN: Receiving.

246
00:21:19.558 --> 00:21:21.017
This is the Maersk Alabama.

247
00:21:21.185 --> 00:21:26.106
Our position is 2 degrees 2 north
by 49 degrees 19 east.

248
00:21:26.273 --> 00:21:29.609
Our course is 180.
Our speed is 17 knots.

249
00:21:29.777 --> 00:21:33.697
We have two skiffs approaching
at a distance of 1.5 miles

250
00:21:33.864 --> 00:21:35.991
with a possible mothership following.

251
00:21:36.158 --> 00:21:38.827
Potential piracy situation.
WOMAN: Copy. Alabama.

252
00:21:38.995 --> 00:21:41.788
Alert your crew.
get your fire hoses ready

253
00:21:41.956 --> 00:21:44.082
and follow lockdown procedures.

254
00:21:45.376 --> 00:21:47.460
Uh... Yeah. Is that it?

255
00:21:47.628 --> 00:21:51.423
I'm relaying your transmission now.
but chances are it's just fishermen.

256
00:21:51.590 --> 00:21:53.466
They're not here to fish.

257
00:21:56.554 --> 00:21:58.555
[♪♪♪]

258
00:22:13.571 --> 00:22:16.740
She's really big! Get ready!

259
00:22:16.907 --> 00:22:20.243
You worry about yourself.
skinny rat!

260
00:22:29.795 --> 00:22:31.588
Both skiffs carrying armed men.

261
00:22:31.756 --> 00:22:35.633
Distance?
One and a quarter miles and closing.

262
00:22:35.843 --> 00:22:37.093
[DIALING]

263
00:22:37.428 --> 00:22:38.470
[PHONE RINGS]

264
00:22:38.971 --> 00:22:42.098
Yeah. Cap.
I wanna bring it up to 125.

265
00:22:44.226 --> 00:22:47.604
You're still good.
One twenty-five.

266
00:23:00.367 --> 00:23:04.079
MUSE: Brothers. we're going
to make a lot of money!

267
00:23:04.288 --> 00:23:06.206
Slow down! The waves are too big!

268
00:23:10.002 --> 00:23:13.546
They're at one mile now. Cap.
Only one mile.

269
00:23:31.315 --> 00:23:33.817
Coalition Warship 237.
this is Maersk Alabama.

270
00:23:34.026 --> 00:23:36.361
Coalition Warship 237.
Maersk Alabama.

271
00:23:39.573 --> 00:23:40.907
[IN DEEP VOICE]
Go. Alabama.

272
00:23:41.117 --> 00:23:45.829
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Our position is 2 degrees 2 north
by 49 degrees 19 east.

273
00:23:45.996 --> 00:23:51.417
[OVER RADIO]
Our course is 180.
Our speed is 18.5 knots.

274
00:23:51.585 --> 00:23:54.879
We are being approached
by two pirate skiffs

275
00:23:55.047 --> 00:23:57.632
with a possible mothership following.

276
00:23:57.800 --> 00:24:00.468
We require immediate assistance.

277
00:24:00.678 --> 00:24:02.637
We have a crew of 20.

278
00:24:02.805 --> 00:24:07.600
We are preparing our weapons now
but request air support if possible.

279
00:24:08.310 --> 00:24:09.727
Copy?

280
00:24:13.440 --> 00:24:15.775
[IN DEEP VOICE]
Copy. Alabama.

281
00:24:15.943 --> 00:24:21.030
Be aware. a gunship is in the air.
ETA your position. five minutes.

282
00:24:21.198 --> 00:24:23.783
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Five minutes. Thank you. 237.

283
00:24:23.993 --> 00:24:25.660
[♪♪♪]

284
00:24:31.041 --> 00:24:32.333
[ASAD SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

285
00:24:32.543 --> 00:24:35.336
ASAD:
Did you hear that? Did you hear that?

286
00:24:37.548 --> 00:24:39.340
We've got to get out of here!

287
00:24:39.508 --> 00:24:42.969
Turn back. turn back!

288
00:24:43.762 --> 00:24:46.556
What are you doing?

289
00:24:46.765 --> 00:24:48.433
[MEN SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

290
00:24:48.601 --> 00:24:50.476
Where are you going?

291
00:24:52.229 --> 00:24:53.855
Come on! Keep going!

292
00:24:56.942 --> 00:24:59.485
SHANE:
Yeah. we got one down.

293
00:24:59.695 --> 00:25:02.989
But the other one's still coming.
Half a mile out.

294
00:25:03.157 --> 00:25:05.116
PHILLIPS:
We need to make a bigger wake.

295
00:25:05.326 --> 00:25:06.367
[PHONE RINGS]

296
00:25:06.535 --> 00:25:08.786
Yeah.
Cancel the limits. One two nine.

297
00:25:12.333 --> 00:25:14.918
Yeah. you're on the edge
with Cylinder Number 5.

298
00:25:15.085 --> 00:25:16.419
Do it.

299
00:25:17.129 --> 00:25:19.380
Port. 5 degrees.
MAN: Port. 5 degrees.

300
00:25:28.265 --> 00:25:29.891
[SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

301
00:25:30.059 --> 00:25:33.144
Faster. faster!

302
00:25:35.981 --> 00:25:37.565
They're at a quarter mile now.

303
00:25:37.775 --> 00:25:40.568
Starboard. 5 degrees.
MAN: Starboard. 5 degrees.

304
00:25:44.698 --> 00:25:46.616
MUSE:
Hurry. hurry! Go!

305
00:25:48.494 --> 00:25:51.371
ELMI:
We're pushing this engine too hard!

306
00:26:06.762 --> 00:26:08.304
Faster. faster!

307
00:26:18.315 --> 00:26:19.774
[ALL GRUNTING]

308
00:26:20.734 --> 00:26:22.735
[ENGINE SPUTTERING]

309
00:26:27.574 --> 00:26:28.741
[CHATTERING IN SOMALI]

310
00:26:32.788 --> 00:26:34.372
Come on. let's go!

311
00:26:36.375 --> 00:26:38.543
[ENGINE SPUTTERS]

312
00:26:38.711 --> 00:26:40.128
This thing is busted.

313
00:26:40.296 --> 00:26:42.714
Then fix it!
I'm trying!

314
00:26:47.386 --> 00:26:48.845
[♪♪♪]

315
00:26:49.513 --> 00:26:51.514
[MAN SPEAKING IN SOMALI]

316
00:27:11.660 --> 00:27:14.495
KENNY:
They're not messing around.
Lit us up from miles away.

317
00:27:14.663 --> 00:27:15.997
MAN 1:
Must've been tracking us.

318
00:27:16.165 --> 00:27:18.499
MAN 2:
Why doesn't the company
give us armed guards?

319
00:27:18.667 --> 00:27:20.418
SHANE:
Move it in. The captain's here.

320
00:27:20.627 --> 00:27:23.296
Blips on the radar that are clocking
at 27 knots.

321
00:27:23.464 --> 00:27:25.965
They were moving.
We cannot outrun these guys.

322
00:27:26.633 --> 00:27:31.220
Obviously. we all just went
through a dangerous situation.

323
00:27:31.722 --> 00:27:35.683
Two skiffs. both with armed intruders.

324
00:27:35.851 --> 00:27:40.563
Now. we all know that's a hazard
in these waters. but you performed well.

325
00:27:41.231 --> 00:27:42.940
The ship performed well.

326
00:27:43.650 --> 00:27:45.651
The authorities
have been made aware

327
00:27:45.819 --> 00:27:48.404
so I think we have the situation
well in hand.

328
00:27:48.572 --> 00:27:51.115
From now on.
we just follow our normal duties.

329
00:27:51.283 --> 00:27:53.409
Mate. what do you got?

330
00:27:53.577 --> 00:27:57.455
Yeah. We're all on double shifts
until we make it through these waters.

331
00:27:57.623 --> 00:28:00.833
All right. Chief. can you keep
your engineers on roster?

332
00:28:01.001 --> 00:28:03.461
We'll keep a guy in the ECR
around the clock.

333
00:28:03.670 --> 00:28:06.964
All right. Enjoy your coffee.

334
00:28:07.132 --> 00:28:08.508
CRONAN:
Cap.

335
00:28:10.552 --> 00:28:11.677
They're coming back.

336
00:28:11.845 --> 00:28:14.555
MAN 3:
Amen. Yeah. that's right.
They're coming back.

337
00:28:14.765 --> 00:28:19.227
If they come back. we'll follow procedure.
They worked today. they'll work again.

338
00:28:19.395 --> 00:28:23.731
We got the speed. we got the height.
we got hoses that can sink those skiffs.

339
00:28:23.899 --> 00:28:27.819
We will follow the procedures even if
we have to shut down. lock down.

340
00:28:27.986 --> 00:28:29.779
go dead in the water
and wait for help.

341
00:28:29.947 --> 00:28:30.988
[MEN CLAMORING]

342
00:28:31.156 --> 00:28:33.491
Now. wait. I'm a u...
Okay. I'm a union guy. okay?

343
00:28:33.659 --> 00:28:35.159
Twenty-five years. all right?

344
00:28:35.369 --> 00:28:39.163
I'm telling you now that they're
not paying me enough to fight pirates.

345
00:28:39.331 --> 00:28:42.250
You all signed up for a route
around the Horn of Africa.

346
00:28:42.418 --> 00:28:45.878
What did you expect?
I didn't sign up for the Navy over here.

347
00:28:46.046 --> 00:28:47.672
You signed up for the route.

348
00:28:47.840 --> 00:28:49.340
For a cargo ship.
SHANE: What did you expect?

349
00:28:49.508 --> 00:28:51.968
MAN 4:
Not getting attacked
without weapons.

350
00:28:52.136 --> 00:28:54.720
Why don't we get out of here?
Put room between us.

351
00:28:54.888 --> 00:28:56.806
Go where?
In eight hours.

352
00:28:56.974 --> 00:29:00.351
we could be a hundred miles from here.
KENNY: Hundred to a 150.

353
00:29:00.519 --> 00:29:03.229
There's five pirate bands
in this part of the world.

354
00:29:03.397 --> 00:29:06.941
You go out 300 miles. you run into one.
go 6. you run into another.

355
00:29:07.109 --> 00:29:10.653
Our job is to move the cargo
as fast as possible. That's the job.

356
00:29:10.821 --> 00:29:13.573
If anybody doesn't like it.
if anybody wants off.

357
00:29:13.740 --> 00:29:14.949
if anybody doesn't like this route

358
00:29:15.117 --> 00:29:17.827
between Salalah. Djibouti
and Mombasa.

359
00:29:17.995 --> 00:29:21.164
come to my office and
sign the paperwork per the union.

360
00:29:21.331 --> 00:29:25.001
and you'll be on the first flight home
out of Mombasa.

361
00:29:31.675 --> 00:29:33.968
Enjoy your coffee.
Let's get back to work.

362
00:29:34.178 --> 00:29:37.180
KENNY:
Go get those guys squared away.
will you?

363
00:30:15.594 --> 00:30:16.636
[LADDER CLANGS]

364
00:30:16.803 --> 00:30:20.515
ASAD:
The ocean was rough. Really rough.

365
00:30:20.682 --> 00:30:24.644
Hufan. I'm telling you.
our boat couldn't take it.

366
00:30:24.811 --> 00:30:27.522
Nothing was working for us.

367
00:30:28.148 --> 00:30:30.858
MUSE:
Hurry up.

368
00:30:31.068 --> 00:30:33.694
We need a bigger one for that ship.

369
00:30:33.862 --> 00:30:36.572
I want this welded by the morning

370
00:30:36.740 --> 00:30:38.115
by tomorrow. got it?

371
00:30:38.617 --> 00:30:40.618
[MAN SPEAKING IN SOMALI]

372
00:30:41.787 --> 00:30:43.204
Elmi.

373
00:30:43.372 --> 00:30:45.456
When will that engine be ready?

374
00:30:45.999 --> 00:30:47.708
We've gotta fix it.

375
00:30:47.876 --> 00:30:50.545
This thing is old and weak.

376
00:30:50.712 --> 00:30:52.296
It's a piece of shit.

377
00:30:52.923 --> 00:30:57.593
Shut up and fix it
for your crew of women.

378
00:30:57.761 --> 00:30:59.220
[LAUGHS]

379
00:31:02.975 --> 00:31:05.476
Why don't you give me your engine?

380
00:31:05.686 --> 00:31:10.314
Shut up. Skinny. You talk too much.

381
00:31:10.983 --> 00:31:13.776
I may be skinny. but I'm not a coward.

382
00:31:20.784 --> 00:31:22.034
What did you say?

383
00:31:22.202 --> 00:31:23.327
[GUN COCKS]

384
00:31:23.495 --> 00:31:24.829
Say it again!

385
00:31:24.997 --> 00:31:26.455
[ASAD SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

386
00:31:26.665 --> 00:31:29.125
You think you're somebody?

387
00:31:30.961 --> 00:31:32.878
Say it again!

388
00:31:45.475 --> 00:31:47.351
[MEN MURMURING]

389
00:31:49.396 --> 00:31:50.438
[WRENCH CLATTERS]

390
00:31:51.106 --> 00:31:55.776
The coward is the first one in the grave.

391
00:32:25.557 --> 00:32:26.891
[SIGHS]

392
00:32:30.520 --> 00:32:32.480
SHANE [OVER RADIO]:
Captain. this is Shane.

393
00:32:35.817 --> 00:32:37.693
Yeah. go ahead.

394
00:32:37.861 --> 00:32:39.904
I think you better get up here.

395
00:32:40.656 --> 00:32:42.031
Coming.

396
00:32:42.240 --> 00:32:44.241
[♪♪♪]

397
00:32:48.997 --> 00:32:50.873
Where are they?
Port quarter.

398
00:32:51.041 --> 00:32:52.750
One-point-seven miles. captain.

399
00:32:56.797 --> 00:32:58.422
Guy's coming on his own.

400
00:33:03.387 --> 00:33:04.428
PHILLIPS:
Sound the alarm.

401
00:33:05.639 --> 00:33:07.556
Get U.S. Maritime Emergency for me.

402
00:33:10.477 --> 00:33:11.477
[DIALING ON PHONE]

403
00:33:11.645 --> 00:33:12.895
[HORN BLARES
THEN SIREN WAILING]

404
00:33:13.063 --> 00:33:16.107
Muster stations. This is not a drill.
Everyone to muster stations.

405
00:33:16.274 --> 00:33:18.442
[OVER PA] This is not a drill.
Come on.

406
00:33:18.985 --> 00:33:20.194
MAN 1:
Shit.

407
00:33:20.362 --> 00:33:22.697
MAN 2:
Come on. Let's go. Go.

408
00:33:23.323 --> 00:33:24.365
[PHONE RINGS]

409
00:33:24.533 --> 00:33:25.991
Yeah. Cap.
They're coming back.

410
00:33:26.159 --> 00:33:28.285
I want max revs. Take the limits off.

411
00:33:28.453 --> 00:33:30.830
Copy that. Canceling all limits.

412
00:33:30.997 --> 00:33:33.791
Five degrees starboard.
Starboard. 5 degrees.

413
00:33:34.126 --> 00:33:35.751
[♪♪♪]

414
00:33:44.553 --> 00:33:45.845
Get ready.

415
00:33:54.604 --> 00:33:57.064
U.S. Maritime Emergency line.

416
00:33:58.233 --> 00:34:01.694
This is the Maersk Alabama.
We are under pirate attack at a...

417
00:34:01.862 --> 00:34:04.613
What's happening?
SHANE: Ken. get out here.

418
00:34:04.823 --> 00:34:07.825
I need eyes on the wing. Skiff coming in.
I'm on it.

419
00:34:07.993 --> 00:34:12.413
PHILLIPS:
Our course is 166.
Our speed is 19 knots.

420
00:34:12.622 --> 00:34:15.541
Copy that. Alabama.
Relaying to military channels now.

421
00:34:15.709 --> 00:34:17.668
Copy that.

422
00:34:18.587 --> 00:34:20.212
SHANE:
They're coming in fast. Cap.

423
00:34:20.589 --> 00:34:21.630
[STATIC CRACKLING OVER RADIO]

424
00:34:21.798 --> 00:34:23.841
MUSE [IN ENGLISH OVER RADIO]:
Alabama.

425
00:34:24.092 --> 00:34:26.135
Alabama ship.

426
00:34:26.303 --> 00:34:29.889
Somali coast guard.
This is a routine check.

427
00:34:30.098 --> 00:34:31.932
Stop your ship now.

428
00:34:32.851 --> 00:34:37.104
We are coming aboard.
We're here to help you.

429
00:34:37.272 --> 00:34:39.732
Shane. they're dead astern.
Jesus Christ.

430
00:34:43.820 --> 00:34:45.863
MIKE: Yeah. Cap.
We're gonna need the hoses.

431
00:34:46.072 --> 00:34:48.073
Yeah. your pumps are good.

432
00:34:49.409 --> 00:34:53.204
Count it down for me. Shane.
SHANE: Yeah. They're at 800 yards.

433
00:34:53.413 --> 00:34:55.498
Prepare for hard turns.
MUSE: Stop now!

434
00:34:55.665 --> 00:34:56.791
SHANE:
Standing by.

435
00:34:56.958 --> 00:35:00.503
MUSE:
Alabama. this is your final warning.

436
00:35:00.670 --> 00:35:02.046
Stop the ship.

437
00:35:03.799 --> 00:35:06.342
They're not stopping.

438
00:35:07.093 --> 00:35:09.011
Show them who we are. Muse.

439
00:35:12.140 --> 00:35:13.933
[IN SOMALI]
Shoot at them!

440
00:35:15.268 --> 00:35:17.520
[GUNFIRE]

441
00:35:17.729 --> 00:35:21.106
Shots fired! Shots fired! Hit the hoses.

442
00:35:22.901 --> 00:35:23.984
[MACHINE WHIRRING]

443
00:35:28.490 --> 00:35:30.282
Turn!

444
00:35:33.286 --> 00:35:34.370
[SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

445
00:35:40.710 --> 00:35:41.919
KENNY:
Coming in close. Cap.

446
00:35:43.380 --> 00:35:44.755
[GRUNTING]

447
00:35:51.137 --> 00:35:52.263
[SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

448
00:35:56.184 --> 00:35:58.269
Shane! Hose seven has slipped.

449
00:35:58.478 --> 00:36:00.479
Bay 17. I'm on it. Shit.

450
00:36:00.647 --> 00:36:03.816
Be careful.
I'm on Channel 3.

451
00:36:08.613 --> 00:36:10.739
It's clear over there!

452
00:36:15.579 --> 00:36:17.746
KENNY:
They're coming back in.

453
00:36:25.672 --> 00:36:28.632
MUSE:
Untie the ladder.

454
00:36:44.566 --> 00:36:45.774
Give me the other one.

455
00:36:51.156 --> 00:36:52.323
[SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

456
00:37:00.498 --> 00:37:02.374
Shoot him!

457
00:37:09.007 --> 00:37:10.549
Let's go. let's go!

458
00:37:11.009 --> 00:37:12.676
Hurry up. Bilal.

459
00:37:12.844 --> 00:37:14.887
Move your ass. kid.

460
00:37:15.096 --> 00:37:17.097
[GRUNTING]

461
00:37:24.773 --> 00:37:26.774
[MUSE SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

462
00:37:26.983 --> 00:37:30.277
Channel 3. Shane. get out of there.

463
00:37:30.445 --> 00:37:32.571
Get everybody
down to the engine room.

464
00:37:32.739 --> 00:37:34.823
I need you in command there.

465
00:37:37.285 --> 00:37:39.870
MUSE:
Stop him!

466
00:37:43.208 --> 00:37:44.583
[GROANS]

467
00:37:46.962 --> 00:37:48.295
All crew! All crew!

468
00:37:48.505 --> 00:37:52.383
All crew to the engine room!
All crew to the engine room now!

469
00:37:53.802 --> 00:37:55.302
MAN 1:
Come on. let's go. Move it.

470
00:37:55.887 --> 00:37:56.929
MAN 2:
Come on. men.

471
00:37:58.098 --> 00:38:00.140
[PIRATES SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

472
00:38:03.144 --> 00:38:05.604
MUSE:
Higher. Get it higher.

473
00:38:09.359 --> 00:38:11.902
Port. 30 degrees.
KENNY: Port. 30 degrees.

474
00:38:23.164 --> 00:38:25.040
Hook it on!

475
00:38:31.464 --> 00:38:34.675
They got the ladder up.
Starboard. 30 degrees.

476
00:38:34.884 --> 00:38:36.385
KENNY:
Starboard. 30 degrees.

477
00:38:45.228 --> 00:38:46.854
Get out of my way.

478
00:38:50.525 --> 00:38:52.526
[PIRATES SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

479
00:38:59.200 --> 00:39:02.828
Port. 30 degrees.
KENNY: Port. 30 degrees.

480
00:39:08.293 --> 00:39:10.919
Starboard. 30 degrees.
Starboard. 30.

481
00:39:23.683 --> 00:39:25.309
MAN:
Someone's shooting at us.

482
00:39:25.477 --> 00:39:28.103
CRONAN:
Hang on. Just get together
against the wall.

483
00:39:28.813 --> 00:39:30.606
Cronan. Cronan.
CRONAN: Yeah.

484
00:39:30.774 --> 00:39:33.233
SHANE:
Hold them by the door.
We'll get a head count.

485
00:39:33.401 --> 00:39:34.735
Go down to the door.

486
00:39:35.236 --> 00:39:36.487
Mike?
MIKE: Yeah.

487
00:39:36.654 --> 00:39:39.740
How long till you can shut her down?
Five minutes.

488
00:39:49.709 --> 00:39:52.628
[PIRATES SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

489
00:40:00.178 --> 00:40:02.346
Four pirates onboard.

490
00:40:02.514 --> 00:40:05.933
[OVER PA] Four pirates. coming
towards us down the main deck.

491
00:40:06.101 --> 00:40:07.643
Lock down the bridge.
SHANE: Yeah.

492
00:40:07.811 --> 00:40:11.355
PHILLIPS:
Listen up. We have been boarded
by four armed pirates.

493
00:40:12.816 --> 00:40:13.857
You know the drill.

494
00:40:14.526 --> 00:40:18.529
We stay hidden no matter what.
I don't want any hostages.

495
