00:55:53.547 --> 00:55:56.966
take the money out of the safe
and call it a day. All right?

737
00:55:58.385 --> 00:55:59.719
[BILAL GROANING]

738
00:55:59.970 --> 00:56:02.013
[PANTING]

739
00:56:05.517 --> 00:56:08.144
You're bad luck. Irish.

740
00:56:09.688 --> 00:56:11.230
[IN SOMALI]
Hey. take him upstairs.

741
00:56:11.398 --> 00:56:13.149
I can't move.

742
00:56:13.317 --> 00:56:15.777
Take him upstairs
and tell Najee to come.

743
00:56:15.944 --> 00:56:18.112
[IN ENGLISH] You go with him.
We're gonna go?

744
00:56:18.280 --> 00:56:20.073
MUSE:
Go!

745
00:56:22.076 --> 00:56:23.534
BILAL [IN ENGLISH]:
Hey.

746
00:56:23.702 --> 00:56:25.244
Wait. Aah!

747
00:56:25.412 --> 00:56:27.205
You're not gonna find anybody.

748
00:56:27.372 --> 00:56:30.041
Don't talk. Go.

749
00:56:42.554 --> 00:56:47.183
[IN ENGLISH]
Your friend make fool of us?
Make us run around?

750
00:56:47.351 --> 00:56:50.895
[IN SOMALI]
If one of them moves.
send them to their graves.

751
00:56:53.565 --> 00:56:55.274
Here.

752
00:58:06.763 --> 00:58:08.639
[THUDDING]

753
00:58:15.772 --> 00:58:17.273
MAN:
Hey.

754
00:58:18.317 --> 00:58:19.692
[MUSE GRUNTS]

755
00:58:19.860 --> 00:58:21.319
[♪♪♪]

756
00:58:21.528 --> 00:58:23.321
[GROANS THEN SHOUTS IN SOMALI]

757
00:58:24.865 --> 00:58:26.741
We got a problem.

758
00:58:27.201 --> 00:58:29.118
Your buddy's hurt real bad.

759
00:58:29.328 --> 00:58:30.536
[GROANING]

760
00:58:30.704 --> 00:58:35.875
We better get this dressed.
We got a sick bay here onboard.
and this guy knows what to do.

761
00:58:36.084 --> 00:58:37.460
NAJEE:
What happened to you?

762
00:58:37.628 --> 00:58:41.839
[IN SOMALI]
They put glass down for me.
They got me.

763
00:58:42.007 --> 00:58:43.549
Where is Muse?

764
00:58:43.717 --> 00:58:44.926
In the engine room.

765
00:58:45.969 --> 00:58:48.971
He wants Najee to come down.

766
00:58:49.514 --> 00:58:51.682
SHANE [OVER RADIO]:
Bridge. Bridge. come in.

767
00:58:51.892 --> 00:58:54.352
Alabama bridge. come in.
Do you read?

768
00:58:55.312 --> 00:59:00.274
This is the crew of the Maersk Alabama.
We have your captain.

769
00:59:00.442 --> 00:59:02.777
Put your hand over his mouth.

770
00:59:03.362 --> 00:59:04.904
[IN ENGLISH] Hey.
[IN ENGLISH] No.

771
00:59:05.072 --> 00:59:06.447
SHANE:
We have your leader.

772
00:59:06.615 --> 00:59:09.742
We have your captain and his weapon.
We wanna trade.

773
00:59:09.910 --> 00:59:11.994
Captain for captain. We want a deal.

774
00:59:12.162 --> 00:59:15.498
Take that off of his head.
Cronan. take that off his head now.

775
00:59:15.666 --> 00:59:16.791
I no kill.

776
00:59:16.959 --> 00:59:19.502
Talk. Talk to your friends
so they know it's you.

777
00:59:19.670 --> 00:59:22.630
Talk to your friends.
Come on. asshole. Say something.

778
00:59:22.798 --> 00:59:24.674
I love America.

779
00:59:26.677 --> 00:59:29.637
[IN SOMALI]
Hey! Get me out of here!

780
00:59:29.805 --> 00:59:32.682
Listen to what these guys have to say.

781
00:59:33.183 --> 00:59:34.850
[IN SOMALI]
What happened?

782
00:59:35.018 --> 00:59:37.311
MUSE:
They cut my hand. bad.

783
00:59:37.479 --> 00:59:41.190
We'll straighten everything out later.
Just get me out of here.

784
00:59:41.358 --> 00:59:43.567
Give Irish the radio.

785
00:59:45.487 --> 00:59:47.571
I'll give it to him now.

786
00:59:47.739 --> 00:59:48.781
[IN ENGLISH]
Talk.

787
00:59:48.949 --> 00:59:50.574
[MUMBLING IN SOMALI]

788
00:59:51.785 --> 00:59:55.663
Uh... Uh... Captain. you know.
if you wanna get off this ship.

789
00:59:55.831 --> 00:59:59.625
you don't have a skiff anymore.
but you could get into our lifeboat.

790
00:59:59.793 --> 01:00:03.129
You could take off
off our stern.

791
01:00:03.297 --> 01:00:07.842
and you can go with the $30.000.
and you could get off this ship right now.

792
01:00:08.885 --> 01:00:10.886
Do we have a deal?

793
01:00:11.305 --> 01:00:13.806
Say we have a deal.
Say we have a deal.

794
01:00:13.974 --> 01:00:16.726
[IN ENGLISH]
Okay. Irish. Deal.

795
01:00:16.935 --> 01:00:20.021
Deal. Irish. deal.
Okay. then.

796
01:00:21.273 --> 01:00:23.858
Listen. we could...
NAJEE: Hey.

797
01:00:26.862 --> 01:00:29.655
[IN SOMALI]
Thirty thousand is nothing.

798
01:00:29.823 --> 01:00:32.116
I want millions!

799
01:00:32.826 --> 01:00:34.827
[♪♪♪]

800
01:01:01.313 --> 01:01:04.273
There. All right. there's the lifeboat.

801
01:01:05.859 --> 01:01:09.612
Hey. Bilal. check it out.

802
01:01:09.780 --> 01:01:13.574
If anyone moves. kill them.

803
01:01:13.742 --> 01:01:15.785
Kill them!

804
01:01:16.995 --> 01:01:20.706
[IN ENGLISH]
Where is our captain?
Where is our guy?

805
01:01:20.916 --> 01:01:22.917
[GROANS]

806
01:01:23.126 --> 01:01:24.668
SHANE:
Hey. Cap. Cap. it's Shane.

807
01:01:24.836 --> 01:01:28.339
I'm not armed. I'm not armed.
No weapons. No. Hey. easy.

808
01:01:29.132 --> 01:01:31.801
There's no weapons.
There's no weapons. No weapons.

809
01:01:32.010 --> 01:01:34.428
[PIRATES SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

810
01:01:34.638 --> 01:01:37.306
Hey. Shane. Do you have
the captain? Where is he?

811
01:01:37.474 --> 01:01:40.309
In the engine room.
Bring him up so they can see him.

812
01:01:40.477 --> 01:01:41.685
I wanna see.
You will.

813
01:01:41.853 --> 01:01:44.605
Bring him up so they can see him.
He's on his way.

814
01:01:44.773 --> 01:01:45.815
[SHOUTS IN SOMALI]

815
01:01:45.982 --> 01:01:48.401
Where?
Here he is. Yeah. there he is.

816
01:01:48.568 --> 01:01:51.695
NAJEE: Where?!
PHILLIPS: See? There he is. There.

817
01:01:51.905 --> 01:01:53.572
[IN SOMALI]
What's going on. Skinny?

818
01:01:53.740 --> 01:01:56.033
[IN SOMALI]
Do what they say
and get me out of here.

819
01:01:56.201 --> 01:01:57.535
Be strong. man.

820
01:01:57.702 --> 01:02:01.580
Now let's do this.
We'll bring up your guy.
You get in. you buckle up.

821
01:02:01.748 --> 01:02:05.042
We drop you in. and then
you're on your way. Okay? Okay?

822
01:02:05.210 --> 01:02:09.046
[IN ENGLISH]
No. You come with us.
Till we get our guy back.

823
01:02:09.214 --> 01:02:12.133
No. no. no. You'll get your guy back.
No way!

824
01:02:12.300 --> 01:02:13.467
Hey! Hey!
MAN: Get in!

825
01:02:13.969 --> 01:02:16.554
[GUNFIRE THEN ALL SHOUTING]

826
01:02:16.763 --> 01:02:18.472
Listen! Hey!

827
01:02:18.640 --> 01:02:22.309
You come. or I kill everybody!
I don't care!

828
01:02:22.477 --> 01:02:23.894
It's your choice!

829
01:02:24.062 --> 01:02:27.106
All right! All right!
You go! You go! You're going!

830
01:02:27.274 --> 01:02:30.818
PHILLIPS:
Chief. bring the guy up now.
It's gonna be okay. Bring him up.

831
01:02:30.986 --> 01:02:34.321
Shane. you got the crew.
Don't go. Cap. Don't get in there.

832
01:02:34.489 --> 01:02:37.283
We gotta get them off the ship.
SHANE: Not like this.

833
01:02:37.451 --> 01:02:40.202
Cap. you can't do this.
Goddamn it. Cap!

834
01:02:45.125 --> 01:02:46.834
All right. who's driving this thing?

835
01:02:47.002 --> 01:02:49.962
[SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

836
01:02:50.589 --> 01:02:52.590
NAJEE [IN SOMALI]:
Watch him.

837
01:02:53.758 --> 01:02:56.218
Bilal. hold the gun on him.

838
01:02:56.386 --> 01:02:59.555
PHILLIPS:
Now. look. it's very simple to operate.

839
01:02:59.723 --> 01:03:02.016
On. off. start. stop.

840
01:03:02.184 --> 01:03:04.018
Compass to follow your heading.

841
01:03:04.186 --> 01:03:07.188
You see your throttle there.
You got a squawk box.

842
01:03:07.355 --> 01:03:08.481
Gas. gas. Enough gas?

843
01:03:08.648 --> 01:03:10.858
Plenty of fuel to get you to Somalia.

844
01:03:11.026 --> 01:03:12.776
SHANE [OVER RADIO]:
Cap. we got the guy.

845
01:03:12.944 --> 01:03:15.029
All right. Send him on in.
I'm coming out.

846
01:03:15.197 --> 01:03:17.698
Okay. send him in. Let him go.

847
01:03:17.866 --> 01:03:19.033
[SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

848
01:03:19.201 --> 01:03:20.534
[IN ENGLISH]
Let him go!

849
01:03:20.702 --> 01:03:23.370
Go. Send the captain out.

850
01:03:23.538 --> 01:03:27.541
All right. now. that handle. see?
You're gonna move that up and down.

851
01:03:27.709 --> 01:03:31.921
You gotta pump it. one. two.
three. four. five. and then you drop.

852
01:03:32.130 --> 01:03:34.089
SHANE:
Cap. come on out.

853
01:03:36.176 --> 01:03:39.803
Cap? Cap. what's going on in there?

854
01:03:40.013 --> 01:03:43.224
Just however many times it takes.

855
01:03:43.391 --> 01:03:46.143
pump it. then you're in the water.
and off you go.

856
01:03:49.105 --> 01:03:50.731
Go!

857
01:03:51.900 --> 01:03:52.942
Go back!

858
01:03:53.109 --> 01:03:55.027
[GUNFIRE]

859
01:03:55.195 --> 01:03:56.529
SHANE:
Hey. Cap!

860
01:03:56.738 --> 01:03:58.280
[PIRATES SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

861
01:04:05.830 --> 01:04:07.498
CRONAN:
Goddamn it! No!

862
01:04:08.375 --> 01:04:09.875
Cap!
No!

863
01:04:10.043 --> 01:04:12.253
NAJEE:
Sit! Sit!

864
01:04:12.420 --> 01:04:13.837
Here!

865
01:04:14.005 --> 01:04:15.714
Go.

866
01:04:21.304 --> 01:04:25.307
Irish. it's only us now.

867
01:04:27.978 --> 01:04:37.978
[♪♪♪]

868
01:04:48.623 --> 01:04:51.041
MAN 1: Stand clear.
MAN 2: Make a hole.

869
01:04:52.544 --> 01:04:53.919
CASTELLANO:
Make way.

870
01:04:54.129 --> 01:04:55.796
Copy.

871
01:04:56.423 --> 01:04:58.424
[CHATTERING]

872
01:04:58.717 --> 01:05:01.343
Captain's in Combat.
MAN 3: Captain's in Combat.

873
01:05:01.511 --> 01:05:05.014
CTF 151.
this is Bainbridge Charlie-Oscar. Over.

874
01:05:05.181 --> 01:05:07.099
HOWARD:
Captain. this is Admiral Howard.

875
01:05:07.309 --> 01:05:09.852
A U.S. -flagged cargo ship.
the Maersk Alabama.

876
01:05:10.061 --> 01:05:14.356
has been hijacked 820 nautical miles
west of your current position.

877
01:05:14.566 --> 01:05:18.027
Four men have taken the ship's captain
hostage in a lifeboat.

878
01:05:18.194 --> 01:05:20.613
Presumed Somali pirates. Over.

879
01:05:20.947 --> 01:05:23.699
Roger. ma'am. Do we
have any other information? Over.

880
01:05:23.867 --> 01:05:28.454
Not at this time. but best guess
is they're heading for the Somali coast.

881
01:05:28.622 --> 01:05:30.914
Your orders are to proceed
and intercept.

882
01:05:31.082 --> 01:05:34.627
Further to follow. This is CTF 151 out.

883
01:05:36.296 --> 01:05:38.714
Ops. prep ScanEagle.
Need aerial surveillance.

884
01:05:38.923 --> 01:05:40.549
Aye. sir.

885
01:05:42.093 --> 01:05:44.720
CCS. this is the captain.
Come to full power.

886
01:05:44.929 --> 01:05:46.555
TAO. get position.
MAN 4: TAO. aye.

887
01:05:46.765 --> 01:05:51.310
Bridge. captain. full left rudder.
Come to course 285.

888
01:05:51.519 --> 01:05:53.520
[♪♪♪]

889
01:06:17.295 --> 01:06:21.507
Hufan. do you read me?

890
01:06:21.716 --> 01:06:24.385
[STATIC CRACKLING OVER RADIO]

891
01:06:24.552 --> 01:06:26.929
Hufan. can you hear me?

892
01:06:28.139 --> 01:06:30.641
[IN SOMALI]
Where's your boss?
He should be with us by now.

893
01:06:31.434 --> 01:06:33.644
Don't worry. He's coming.

894
01:06:36.523 --> 01:06:38.190
[HISSES]

895
01:06:38.400 --> 01:06:40.693
Stupid hand.

896
01:06:41.528 --> 01:06:44.113
[BILAL GROANING]

897
01:06:45.073 --> 01:06:48.117
Stop whining.
You sound like a little girl.

898
01:06:48.284 --> 01:06:52.663
You wanted to come with us.
You asked for this.

899
01:06:52.831 --> 01:06:55.332
BILAL:
I didn't think this would happen.

900
01:06:55.542 --> 01:06:57.751
I could lose my foot.

901
01:06:57.919 --> 01:07:01.004
MUSE:
You have to be ready for anything.

902
01:07:01.172 --> 01:07:03.757
This game isn't for the weak.

903
01:07:05.802 --> 01:07:07.678
[IN ENGLISH]
You okay. Irish?

904
01:07:09.139 --> 01:07:10.848
Yeah.

905
01:07:12.183 --> 01:07:13.434
Your face looks scared.

906
01:07:14.352 --> 01:07:17.146
But everything gonna be okay.

907
01:07:17.313 --> 01:07:18.522
I'm not gonna hurt you.

908
01:07:23.820 --> 01:07:26.905
In two days we'll be eating
in Somalia.

909
01:07:27.532 --> 01:07:31.702
Rice. Goat meat. You'll like.

910
01:07:32.579 --> 01:07:36.331
My boss talk to ship company.

911
01:07:36.499 --> 01:07:40.252
Insurance man come. bag of dollars.

912
01:07:40.420 --> 01:07:42.254
you go home.

913
01:07:45.383 --> 01:07:47.342
[HORN BLARING]

914
01:07:54.017 --> 01:07:55.392
ELMI [IN SOMALI]:
What is it?

915
01:07:57.270 --> 01:07:58.937
MUSE [IN SOMALI]:
It's a gift.

916
01:08:02.108 --> 01:08:04.109
[♪♪♪]

917
01:08:05.570 --> 01:08:07.112
[IN ENGLISH]
Hey.

918
01:08:08.072 --> 01:08:09.656
[SPEAKS IN SOMALI]

919
01:08:09.824 --> 01:08:15.829
[IN ENGLISH]
Irish. You lie. Irish.
Your ship no broke.

920
01:08:15.997 --> 01:08:18.165
They come Somalia too.

921
01:08:19.083 --> 01:08:20.334
More money.

922
01:08:21.795 --> 01:08:23.796
[♪♪♪]

923
01:08:26.925 --> 01:08:28.926
[BEEPING]

924
01:08:31.137 --> 01:08:34.598
Looks like they're heading north
to the closest point of land.

925
01:08:35.892 --> 01:08:39.937
MIKE:
And that's only gonna take them
36 hours at the most?

926
01:08:43.107 --> 01:08:46.068
SHANE:
Just gotta stay with them
till the Navy gets here.

927
01:09:00.917 --> 01:09:02.918
NAJEE:
Give me some khat.

928
01:09:03.086 --> 01:09:05.420
ELMI:
Why? You've had more than your share.

929
01:09:05.588 --> 01:09:07.673
NAJEE:
Says who? Give me some more!

930
01:09:07.841 --> 01:09:09.132
MUSE [IN SOMALI]:
Shut up!

931
01:09:09.300 --> 01:09:11.385
Both of you. shut up.

932
01:09:11.553 --> 01:09:13.095
ELMI:
Just take it.

933
01:09:14.681 --> 01:09:16.431
This is it?

934
01:09:17.767 --> 01:09:19.643
That's all I have.

935
01:09:19.811 --> 01:09:23.021
Where is the rest?
BILAL: I don't have any.

936
01:09:23.189 --> 01:09:24.231
It's all gone.

937
01:09:24.399 --> 01:09:28.026
NAJEE:
You are useless.
I should have taken it from you.

938
01:09:36.703 --> 01:09:39.788
[IN ENGLISH]
Irish. it's taxes.

939
01:09:40.331 --> 01:09:45.460
This money. taking you. that's all it is.

940
01:09:45.670 --> 01:09:48.589
You come to our waters.
you got to pay.

941
01:09:48.756 --> 01:09:51.675
We were in international waters.

942
01:09:51.843 --> 01:09:53.844
Not your waters. international waters.

943
01:09:54.012 --> 01:09:57.764
We were carrying food
for starving people in Africa.

944
01:09:58.600 --> 01:09:59.892
Even Somalis.

945
01:10:00.101 --> 01:10:05.022
Yeah. sure. Rich countries
like to help Somalis.

946
01:10:05.189 --> 01:10:07.649
Big ships come to our water.

947
01:10:09.193 --> 01:10:11.528
take all the fish out.

948
01:10:11.696 --> 01:10:15.782
What's left for us to fish?
So you're fishermen?

949
01:10:17.327 --> 01:10:19.411
Yeah. we're all fishermen.

950
01:10:23.333 --> 01:10:25.542
[GRUNTS THEN GROANS]

951
01:10:27.712 --> 01:10:29.963
Hey. let me clean out that cut.

952
01:10:30.465 --> 01:10:34.134
Let me get the first-aid kit. clean that out.
It's gonna get infected.

953
01:10:34.302 --> 01:10:35.719
No.

954
01:10:38.056 --> 01:10:40.432
How about the kid?
Can I look at his foot?

955
01:10:40.600 --> 01:10:41.683
NAJEE [IN ENGLISH]:
No.

956
01:10:41.893 --> 01:10:44.353
[IN SOMALI]
They'll fix him when we get back.

957
01:10:44.520 --> 01:10:47.064
Come on. he's barefoot.
You three got sandals.

958
01:10:47.231 --> 01:10:48.649
He's got bare feet.

959
01:10:57.659 --> 01:10:58.951
Go ahead. go.

960
01:11:01.663 --> 01:11:03.205
All right.

961
01:11:05.458 --> 01:11:07.084
Just gonna get the kit.

962
01:11:39.450 --> 01:11:43.203
Go ahead. come here. It's all right.
Your foot. Give me your foot.

963
01:11:43.371 --> 01:11:44.579
Come on.

964
01:11:45.873 --> 01:11:47.791
Let me see it. It's all right.

965
01:11:49.002 --> 01:11:50.794
[GROANING]

966
01:11:53.297 --> 01:11:57.342
How old are you. anyway?
What are you. 16. 17?

967
01:12:00.054 --> 01:12:01.513
[GRUNTS]

968
01:12:01.681 --> 01:12:03.390
You're too young to be out here
doing this.

969
01:12:03.558 --> 01:12:04.933
[IN ENGLISH]
No talking.

970
01:12:05.143 --> 01:12:06.435
No talking.

971
01:12:20.241 --> 01:12:21.783
Hey! Hey!

972
01:12:23.244 --> 01:12:24.286
[IN SOMALI]
He's got a knife!

973
01:12:24.454 --> 01:12:27.748
[IN ENGLISH]
Hey! What you gonna do with this?

974
01:12:28.374 --> 01:12:31.334
[IN SOMALI]
Go back. Get back there.

975
01:12:51.856 --> 01:12:53.440
[BILAL GROANING]

976
01:12:58.863 --> 01:13:01.698
[♪♪♪]

977
01:13:23.930 --> 01:13:26.598
CASTELLANO:
UAV ScanEagle shows
the lifeboat is currently

978
01:13:26.766 --> 01:13:29.726
126 nautical miles
off the Somali coast.

979
01:13:29.894 --> 01:13:32.687
moving on course 305
at five knots.

980
01:13:32.855 --> 01:13:37.526
with the mothership dead in the water
at 60 miles to the northeast.

981
01:13:37.693 --> 01:13:39.569
We have any idea
who these guys are?

982
01:13:39.737 --> 01:13:44.366
SEAL COMMANDER:
The mothership is a Taiwanese fishing
trawler that was hijacked last year.

983
01:13:44.534 --> 01:13:49.746
According to ONI. that vessel's under
the control of Somali warlord Garaad.

984
01:13:49.914 --> 01:13:52.707
We're working on getting the IDs
of the kidnappers.

985
01:13:52.875 --> 01:13:57.045
If this is Garaad's guys. they're looking
for a payday. which means they'll talk.

986
01:13:57.213 --> 01:14:00.173
If we can get them talking.
we can wear them down. Over.

987
01:14:00.341 --> 01:14:04.427
HOWARD:
Frank. this thing is running big here.
and there's a lot of pressure building.

988
01:14:04.595 --> 01:14:07.514
The White House hopes
this can be resolved peacefully

989
01:14:07.682 --> 01:14:11.351
but whatever happens.
Captain Phillips does not
reach Somalia.

990
01:14:12.019 --> 01:14:14.855
I understand. admiral.
but we're gonna need some time.

991
01:14:15.064 --> 01:14:18.191
I think if we press too hard.
we put the hostage at risk.

992
01:14:18.359 --> 01:14:21.194
We're gonna need to use
some tactical patience. Over.

993
01:14:21.362 --> 01:14:24.656
HOWARD:
Do your best to talk them down. Frank.
but you're on the clock.

994
01:14:24.824 --> 01:14:28.869
We're deploying a SEAL team with USS
Boxer and USS Halyburton as support.

995
01:14:29.036 --> 01:14:32.289
If you haven't gotten Phillips back
by the time they arrive.

996
01:14:32.456 --> 01:14:34.249
the SEALs will take care of it.

997
01:14:34.959 --> 01:14:37.169
I understand all. admiral.

998
01:14:45.386 --> 01:14:47.554
[♪♪♪]

999
01:15:02.778 --> 01:15:04.779
[BOAT CREAKING]

1000
01:15:08.951 --> 01:15:10.952
[SIGHS]

1001
01:15:25.760 --> 01:15:27.677
Can I have some water. please?

1002
01:15:29.430 --> 01:15:31.097
Water?

1003
01:15:39.482 --> 01:15:40.815
[GROANS]

1004
01:15:47.615 --> 01:15:49.658
Drive this thing right!

1005
01:15:49.825 --> 01:15:51.660
Calm down. We're on the ocean.

1006
01:15:51.827 --> 01:15:54.204
I should throw you off this boat
right now!

1007
01:15:54.372 --> 01:15:56.039
ELMI:
You need to sit down and relax.

1008
01:15:56.207 --> 01:15:57.624
BILAL [IN ENGLISH]:
Hey. water.

1009
01:15:57.792 --> 01:15:59.793
[NAJEE & ELMI ARGUING IN SOMALI]

1010
01:16:05.258 --> 01:16:06.841
NAJEE [IN ENGLISH]:
Hey. Hey.

1011
01:16:08.427 --> 01:16:11.137
[IN SOMALI]
That's enough.

1012
01:16:11.305 --> 01:16:13.890
Take it away.

1013
01:16:14.058 --> 01:16:16.393
From now on
this water is only for us.

1014
01:16:24.235 --> 01:16:27.237
MUSE [IN SOMALI]:
Stop being such an asshole.

1015
01:16:29.657 --> 01:16:31.866
ELMI:
You've got to control him.

1016
01:16:32.034 --> 01:16:33.576
MUSE:
Just drive and shut up.

1017
01:16:34.704 --> 01:16:37.122
[SPEAKING IN SOMALI]

1018
01:16:37.331 --> 01:16:39.291
Hufan. can you hear me?

1019
01:16:39.458 --> 01:16:41.209
[STATIC CRACKLING OVER RADIO]

1020
01:16:41.377 --> 01:16:43.211
PHILLIPS:
Are you having trouble?

1021
01:16:46.340 --> 01:16:49.551
[IN ENGLISH]
No trouble. Irish. Slow piece of shit.

1022
01:16:51.012 --> 01:16:54.389
Yeah. yeah. Shallow-draft.

1023
01:16:54.557 --> 01:16:58.268
And you're fighting the current.
Gotta take that into account.

1024
01:17:00.938 --> 01:17:03.356
I know what I'm doing.

1025
01:17:03.899 --> 01:17:08.153
Yeah. yeah. sure. you do. Of course.
You're the captain now.

1026
01:17:09.322 --> 01:17:11.072
Oh. hey. captain.

1027
01:17:12.241 --> 01:17:15.994
why don't we open up that hatch
and get a little more air in here?

1028
01:17:17.538 --> 01:17:18.955
[IN SOMALI]
What's wrong with you?

1029
01:17:19.123 --> 01:17:20.540
Don't talk to me.

1030
01:17:24.211 --> 01:17:27.005
A little air might do him some good.

1031
01:17:34.263 --> 01:17:37.098
[IN ENGLISH]
Yeah. open the hatch so your crew...

1032
01:17:37.308 --> 01:17:42.020
No tricks. No. No tricks. Irish.

1033
01:17:44.023 --> 01:17:46.024
[IN SOMALI]
Hufan. can you hear me?

1034
01:17:46.942 --> 01:17:49.694
Hufan. can you hear me?

1035
01:18:07.588 --> 01:18:10.256
MUSE:
We should be heading northwest.

1036
01:18:10.424 --> 01:18:13.468
We've got to get to Garaad's port.

1037
01:18:13.636 --> 01:18:16.096
I am. but there's a lot of wind.

1038
01:18:16.263 --> 01:18:18.431
Just go!
Okay. then let me do it.

1039
01:18:19.809 --> 01:18:22.143
[HUFAN SPEAKING IN SOMALI
OVER RADIO]

1040
01:18:22.311 --> 01:18:24.854
HUFAN [OVER RADIO]:
Muse? Are you there?

1041
01:18:25.022 --> 01:18:26.856
Are you there?

1042
01:18:27.483 --> 01:18:29.609
Hufan. where are you?

1043
01:18:29.777 --> 01:18:32.570
HUFAN:
I'm having trouble with the engine.

1044
01:18:33.072 --> 01:18:36.699
Head home.
I'll be there as soon as I can.

1045
01:18:36.867 --> 01:18:38.618
Hey. we're alone out here.

1046
01:18:38.786 --> 01:18:40.745
We need you to pick us up.

1047
01:18:40.913 --> 01:18:42.997
We've got to get out of this lifeboat.

1048
01:18:43.165 --> 01:18:45.708
Shut up and listen to me.

1049
01:18:45.876 --> 01:18:48.044
You screwed up getting the ship

1050
01:18:48.212 --> 01:18:50.672
so Garaad says
bring back that captain

1051
01:18:50.840 --> 01:18:53.716
or don't come back at all.

1052
01:18:58.305 --> 01:19:01.266
Sounds like there's a problem.
Is there a problem?

1053
01:19:02.852 --> 01:19:04.644
[IN ENGLISH]
Problem.

1054
01:19:05.771 --> 01:19:08.064
No problem. Irish.

1055
01:19:08.649 --> 01:19:11.276
Everything gonna be okay.

1056
01:19:14.363 --> 01:19:15.447
[♪♪♪]

1057
01:19:15.614 --> 01:19:17.615
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

1058
01:19:19.618 --> 01:19:20.660
Yes. sir.

1059
01:19:20.828 --> 01:19:21.911
MAN:
Here's the latest from SOCOM.

1060
01:19:22.079 --> 01:19:25.206
Bainbridge CO has until your arrival
to negotiate a surrender.

1061
01:19:25.416 --> 01:19:27.750
But upon boarding.
you will assume command.

1062
01:19:27.960 --> 01:19:31.463
The White House has authorized
any means necessary to resolve this.

1063
01:19:31.630 --> 01:19:33.131
Roger that.

1064
01:19:43.350 --> 01:19:46.102
Boss. we're setting up comms
in the bird right now.

1065
01:20:18.552 --> 01:20:21.304
I need air.

1066
01:20:21.472 --> 01:20:22.889
[BILAL SPEAKS IN SOMALI]

1067
01:20:23.057 --> 01:20:25.725
When are we going to be home?

1068
01:20:25.893 --> 01:20:28.603
I can't feel my foot anymore.

1069
01:20:28.771 --> 01:20:31.189
It's like hell in here.

1070
01:20:34.318 --> 01:20:36.945
[GRUNTING]

1071
01:20:39.031 --> 01:20:41.407
You wanna tell him
maybe not to do that?

1072
01:20:41.575 --> 01:20:43.409
He wants air.

1073
01:20:43.577 --> 01:20:46.996
Well. that thing is still loaded.
He's got the clip in it.

1074
01:20:47.414 --> 01:20:49.415
[BANGING ON WINDOW]

1075
01:20:49.583 --> 01:20:50.583
[SPEAKING IN SOMALI]

1076
01:20:57.675 --> 01:21:00.760
[IN ENGLISH]
Talk too much. Too much.

1077
01:21:05.849 --> 01:21:07.850
[SPEAKS IN SOMALI]

1078
01:21:11.772 --> 01:21:13.523
[GRUNTS THEN
CONTAINER CLATTERS]

1079
01:21:16.026 --> 01:21:17.735
Gonna need some more water.

1080
01:21:21.657 --> 01:21:23.575
When we get home.

1081
01:21:24.618 --> 01:21:26.828
you'll get a million bottles of it.

1082
01:21:26.996 --> 01:21:30.123
All the water you want.
Really?

1083
01:21:30.291 --> 01:21:34.460
Last year I took a Greek ship.

1084
01:21:36.505 --> 01:21:38.673
Six million dollars.

1085
01:21:39.883 --> 01:21:42.051
Six million dollars?

1086
01:21:44.179 --> 01:21:46.347
So. what are you doing here?

1087
01:21:51.520 --> 01:21:53.521
Shut up. Irish.

1088
01:21:55.024 --> 01:21:56.941
Too much talk.

1089
01:21:58.027 --> 01:22:02.363
Your problem isn't me talking to you.
Your problem is you not listening.

1090
01:22:11.165 --> 01:22:14.792
NAJEE:
You think you have any power here?

1091
01:22:14.960 --> 01:22:18.588
[IN ENGLISH] Let him go.
I should shoot you and be done.

1092
01:22:18.756 --> 01:22:20.757
Take your gun off him.

1093
01:22:20.924 --> 01:22:23.718
I'm the captain.
Who do you think you are?

1094
01:22:23.886 --> 01:22:27.013
You're taking his side?

1095
01:22:28.223 --> 01:22:30.975
You let the American
do whatever he wants!

1096
01:22:31.185 --> 01:22:32.268
[HORN BLARING]

1097
01:22:36.023 --> 01:22:38.024
[SIREN WAILING]

1098
01:22:42.696 --> 01:22:44.864
[IN SOMALI]
I'm losing control!

1099
01:22:46.950 --> 01:22:48.951
[♪♪♪]

1100
01:22:50.996 --> 01:22:52.997
[PIRATES SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

1101
01:23:13.018 --> 01:23:15.019
[HORN BLARES]

1102
01:23:24.530 --> 01:23:25.780
It's the Americans.

1103
01:23:25.948 --> 01:23:28.199
Get something to tie the doors.

1104
01:23:29.326 --> 01:23:33.788
Alabama lifeboat.
this is Frank Castellano.
commander of the USS Bainbridge.

1105
01:23:33.997 --> 01:23:38.126
We wanna get Captain Phillips back
safely and end this thing peacefully.

1106
01:23:38.335 --> 01:23:39.544
[SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

1107
01:23:39.712 --> 01:23:41.295
MUSE [IN ENGLISH]: No move!
All right.

1108
01:23:41.505 --> 01:23:46.175
[BOTH SPEAKING IN SOMALI]

1109
01:23:46.427 --> 01:23:48.636
CASTELLANO [OVER RADIO]:
Alabama lifeboat. come in.

1110
01:23:49.513 --> 01:23:52.765
No military action.
No military action. No al Qaeda.

1111
01:23:52.933 --> 01:23:54.726
We are just fishermen.

1112
01:23:55.269 --> 01:23:56.519
MAN [IN SOMALI]:
Calm down. brother.

1113
01:23:56.687 --> 01:23:59.689
We're here for the captain. not for you.

1114
01:24:00.649 --> 01:24:02.024
They have a spy with them.

1115
01:24:05.404 --> 01:24:07.071
[IN SOMALI]
Hey. you. Who are you?

1116
01:24:07.239 --> 01:24:09.323
My name is Nemo.

1117
01:24:10.159 --> 01:24:12.160
I work with the U.S. Navy.

1118
01:24:13.203 --> 01:24:15.788
We just want to talk.

1119
01:24:15.956 --> 01:24:17.290
MUSE [IN ENGLISH]:
I talk English.

1120
01:24:17.833 --> 01:24:20.543
I want 10 million dollars.

1121
01:24:20.711 --> 01:24:22.128
It's not that easy

1122
01:24:22.755 --> 01:24:25.006
but we'll work on it.

1123
01:24:25.716 --> 01:24:28.801
In the meantime.
what if I bring you
some food and water?

1124
01:24:36.393 --> 01:24:41.189
No tricks. or your captain dead.

1125
01:24:41.398 --> 01:24:43.357
[♪♪♪]

1126
01:24:45.027 --> 01:24:47.028
[PIRATES SPEAKING IN SOMALI]

1127
01:24:48.822 --> 01:24:50.823
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

1128
01:24:55.996 --> 01:24:59.791
MAN [OVER RADIO]:
Request to have pilot ladder lowered
and someone standing by.

1129
01:25:01.835 --> 01:25:03.503
HICKS: Shane Murphy?
Yeah. that's me.

1130
01:25:03.670 --> 01:25:07.381
Lieutenant Hicks. You're entering
a military engagement zone. sir.

1131
01:25:07.549 --> 01:25:12.637
Need you to bring the ship left to 210.
We are here to escort you to Mombasa.

1132
01:25:12.805 --> 01:25:15.264
Your captain'll be in good hands.

1133
01:25:15.432 --> 01:25:17.850
All right. You heard him. guys.

1134
01:25:25.526 --> 01:25:27.610
MAN 1:
OSS. keep the camera on the lifeboat.

1135
01:25:28.278 --> 01:25:29.904
MAN 2 [OVER RADIO]:
ASTAC. aye.

1136
01:25:30.489 --> 01:25:32.698
MAN 1:
Sir. the boat deck is manned
and ready.

1137
01:25:32.866 --> 01:25:36.702
VBSS is on station.
Request permission to lower the RHIBs.

1138
01:25:36.870 --> 01:25:38.830
Execute.
MAN 1: Aye. sir.

1139
01:25:38.997 --> 01:25:41.165
Bridge TAO.
launch the RHIBs.

1140
01:25:41.375 --> 01:25:43.376
[♪♪♪]

1141
01:25:53.971 --> 01:25:55.721
[IN SOMALI]
They're coming.

1142
01:25:55.889 --> 01:25:59.100
Bilal. watch him.

1143
01:25:59.268 --> 01:26:00.309
Watch him closely.

1144
01:26:05.566 --> 01:26:07.775
MUSE [IN ENGLISH]:
Irish. your crew.

1145
01:26:08.902 --> 01:26:10.403
run.

1146
01:26:10.571 --> 01:26:11.779
Ship go.

1147
01:26:11.947 --> 01:26:13.698
PHILLIPS:
It's the Navy clearing the area.

1148
01:26:14.950 --> 01:26:17.243
You better think
about what you're doing.

1149
01:26:18.996 --> 01:26:23.791
Navy good. They protect us.
Back to Somalia.

1150
01:26:23.959 --> 01:26:26.502
The Navy's not here to protect you.

1151
01:26:26.670 --> 01:26:29.171
They're not here to negotiate either.

1152
01:26:31.008 --> 01:26:32.925
No choice.

1153
01:26:33.468 --> 01:26:34.552
I got you.

1154
01:26:51.945 --> 01:26:54.989
NEMO:
Open your door!
We are here with your supplies.

1155
01:26:59.453 --> 01:27:02.580
[CHATTERING IN SOMALI]

1156
01:27:02.789 --> 01:27:05.166
Guns down! America. guns down!

1157
01:27:05.375 --> 01:27:08.169
NEMO:
Calm down. brother.
We're just here to help you.

1158
01:27:08.337 --> 01:27:11.589
Put your guns down now!

1159
01:27:11.798 --> 01:27:13.674
MAN 1:
One outside and one in the hatch.

1160
01:27:14.217 --> 01:27:16.344
MAN 2:
Push the track on the link.

1161
01:27:16.553 --> 01:27:19.597
Listen. we need to see our guy.

1162
01:27:19.765 --> 01:27:22.725
We've got supplies.
food. water for you

1163
01:27:22.893 --> 01:27:24.769
but we need to see our captain.

1164
01:27:24.937 --> 01:27:28.564
Okay. Wait.

1165
01:27:28.732 --> 01:27:29.857
MUSE [IN SOMALI]:
They want to see him.

1166
01:27:30.400 --> 01:27:31.484
Bring him out.

1167
01:27:31.902 --> 01:27:33.653
[PIRATES SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

1168
01:27:33.862 --> 01:27:38.866
All right. All right. All right.
Okay. okay. All right. I'm coming.

1169
01:27:40.535 --> 01:27:41.619
[IN ENGLISH]
Down.

1170
01:27:41.787 --> 01:27:42.954
MAN 3:
Visual confirmation.

1171
01:27:43.121 --> 01:27:44.789
NEMO [IN ENGLISH]:
You all right. captain?

1172
01:27:44.957 --> 01:27:47.249
Yeah. Yeah. I'm okay. Yeah. yeah.

1173
01:27:47.709 --> 01:27:50.962
Listen.
Does my family know where I am?

1174
01:27:51.129 --> 01:27:53.214
Yes. sir. We're keeping them updated.

1175
01:27:53.423 --> 01:27:55.424
PHILLIPS:
It's important they know where I am.

1176
01:27:56.093 --> 01:27:58.260
I'm in Seat 15.

1177
01:27:58.428 --> 01:28:00.096
You understand?

1178
01:28:00.597 --> 01:28:02.515
I'm in Seat 15.

1179
01:28:02.683 --> 01:28:04.725
All stations. TAO. log it: Seat 15.

1180
01:28:04.893 --> 01:28:09.522
Break. CICWO. TAO.
Send that to CTF 151 and SOCOM.

1181
01:28:09.731 --> 01:28:11.691
Don't worry. sir. We'll handle it.

1182
01:28:11.900 --> 01:28:13.442
MUSE [IN SOMALI]:
Get him back inside.

1183
01:28:13.610 --> 01:28:15.111
NAJEE:
Shut up and don't move.

1184
01:28:15.320 --> 01:28:17.613
NEMO [IN SOMALI]:
Calm down. we just want to talk.

1185
01:28:17.781 --> 01:28:20.366
We've got your supplies here.
Food. water.

1186
01:28:20.534 --> 01:28:21.784
[IN ENGLISH]
Where's the money?

1187
01:28:21.952 --> 01:28:25.162
I don't want your food.
I want your money.

1188
01:28:25.330 --> 01:28:28.416
MAN 1: We got another on top.
OSS. maintain camera footage.

1189
01:28:28.583 --> 01:28:30.501
MAN: Hold on a second.
MUSE: No tricks. sahib.

1190
01:28:30.669 --> 01:28:32.253
Ten million dollars. sahib.

1191
01:28:32.421 --> 01:28:33.838
Ten million dollars.

1192
01:28:34.006 --> 01:28:35.756
Listen. you're hurt.

1193
01:28:35.924 --> 01:28:38.009
We've got doctors onboard.

1194
01:28:38.176 --> 01:28:40.678
Let us take care of you.
Hurry up!

1195
01:28:40.846 --> 01:28:43.431
They're treating us like children.

1196
01:28:43.598 --> 01:28:45.141
Ten million dollars. when?

1197
01:28:45.308 --> 01:28:46.642
It's not that easy

1198
01:28:46.810 --> 01:28:48.769
so we need time.

1199
01:28:48.937 --> 01:28:50.938
We've got to talk about this.

1200
01:28:51.106 --> 01:28:52.857
Hurry up. I said!

1201
01:28:53.066 --> 01:28:54.275
[NAJEE SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

1202
01:28:54.484 --> 01:28:56.861
No camera! No camera!

1203
01:28:57.070 --> 01:28:58.863
[SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

1204
01:28:59.072 --> 01:29:00.406
Gunfire. take cover!

1205
01:29:01.033 --> 01:29:04.410
Aah!
Who fired? TAO. who fired?

1206
01:29:04.619 --> 01:29:08.122
Get the RHIBs out of there.
Scram the RHIBs. scram the RHIBs.

1207
01:29:13.587 --> 01:29:15.796
Are you crazy? What are you doing?

1208
01:29:15.964 --> 01:29:18.883
You'll get us all killed!
Do you have to talk all day?

1209
01:29:19.051 --> 01:29:21.969
[IN SOMALI]
You're crazy.
What do you think you're doing?

1210
01:29:22.137 --> 01:29:23.554
All you do is talk!

1211
01:29:23.722 --> 01:29:25.097
CASTELLANO [OVER RADIO]:
Alabama lifeboat. come in.

1212
01:29:25.265 --> 01:29:26.307
Move.

1213
01:29:26.475 --> 01:29:28.809
You have to be strong
to get what you want.

1214
01:29:28.977 --> 01:29:30.269
CASTELLANO:
We have to talk.

1215
01:29:30.604 --> 01:29:33.355
[IN ENGLISH]
Just an accident. Just an accident.

1216
01:29:33.523 --> 01:29:35.107
Is anyone hurt?

1217
01:29:35.275 --> 01:29:37.276
No. American fine. American okay.

1218
01:29:39.071 --> 01:29:40.780
I need to hear it from him.

1219
01:29:40.947 --> 01:29:44.116
I say he okay.
I need to hear it from him.

1220
01:29:45.494 --> 01:29:47.453
[BOTH SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

1221
01:29:47.621 --> 01:29:50.581
NAJEE [IN ENGLISH]:
Get up! Get up!

1222
01:29:52.292 --> 01:29:54.043
Move. Move.

1223
01:29:55.712 --> 01:29:57.922
MUSE: Talk.
Yeah. yeah. it's me.

1224
01:29:58.090 --> 01:29:59.423
Are you okay?

1225
01:29:59.966 --> 01:30:03.844
It's falling apart in here.
He just fired off a round next to my head.

1226
01:30:04.805 --> 01:30:08.307
Is the leader there?
Yeah. he can hear you.

1227
01:30:08.475 --> 01:30:11.811
CASTELLANO:
Captain. listen to me.
We will not tolerate this.

1228
01:30:11.978 --> 01:30:15.397
As captain. you're responsible
for the lives of everyone onboard.

1229
01:30:15.607 --> 01:30:17.942
Right now
you are putting them in jeopardy.

1230
01:30:18.110 --> 01:30:20.152
We wanna resolve this thing
peacefully.

1231
01:30:21.571 --> 01:30:25.116
Let's find a way out of this together
before someone gets hurt.

1232
01:30:28.954 --> 01:30:32.039
Alabama lifeboat. respond.

1233
01:30:34.793 --> 01:30:36.752
I talk when I go Somalia.

1234
01:30:37.671 --> 01:30:38.754
NAJEE:
Sit down.

1235
01:30:38.922 --> 01:30:40.506
MUSE:
Sit down!

1236
01:30:41.716 --> 01:30:43.717
[ELMI SPEAKS IN SOMALI]

1237
01:30:50.267 --> 01:30:52.226
MAN [OVER RADIO]:
TAO. lifeboat is under way.

1238
01:30:52.394 --> 01:30:53.519
TAO. aye.

1239
01:30:53.687 --> 01:30:57.439
Captain. sir. the lifeboat's 12 hours
from the Somali coast.

1240
01:30:57.607 --> 01:30:59.567
Boxer and Halyburton have arrived.

1241
01:30:59.734 --> 01:31:03.404
ETA on the SEAL team is 0400.

1242
01:31:03.613 --> 01:31:05.614
[♪♪♪]

1243
01:31:26.970 --> 01:31:30.347
MUSE:
Irish. no worry.

1244
01:31:30.807 --> 01:31:33.684
Everything gonna be okay.

1245
01:31:38.148 --> 01:31:41.233
After this. I go America.

1246
01:31:42.611 --> 01:31:45.154
I always wanted to go America.

1247
01:31:45.322 --> 01:31:47.656
Go to New York. buy a car...

1248
01:31:52.204 --> 01:31:55.122
[COUGHING]

1249
01:31:55.332 --> 01:31:57.750
[NAJEE SPEAKING IN SOMALI]

1250
01:31:57.918 --> 01:31:59.752
[IN SOMALI]
Hey. this situation has gotten bad.

1251
01:31:59.920 --> 01:32:02.713
There are two more ships.
one on either side.

1252
01:32:02.881 --> 01:32:05.591
ELMI:
That one is huge.

1253
01:32:05.800 --> 01:32:07.801
[CHATTERING IN SOMALI]

1254
01:32:12.265 --> 01:32:13.474
PHILLIPS:
Oh. God.

1255
01:32:13.642 --> 01:32:15.643
ELMI [IN ENGLISH]:
Sit down! Sit down!

1256
01:32:15.810 --> 01:32:18.437
[IN ENGLISH] Sit down!
MUSE [IN ENGLISH]: Down! Down!

1257
01:32:21.441 --> 01:32:23.192
[IN SOMALI]
Bilal. get the ropes.

1258
01:32:23.360 --> 01:32:26.654
Hey. captain. it's all over.
It's all over. captain.

1259
01:32:26.821 --> 01:32:28.113
The other ropes.

1260
01:32:28.323 --> 01:32:31.659
There's a reason your boss took off
and isn't coming back.

1261
01:32:31.826 --> 01:32:35.204
He didn't wanna take on the Navy.
He's gone. He's left you alone.

1262
01:32:35.789 --> 01:32:40.334
You had a plan to take my ship.
That didn't work.
so you thought you could take me?

1263
01:32:40.502 --> 01:32:42.253
[IN ENGLISH] Shut up.
PHILLIPS: Make a run to Somalia?

1264
01:32:42.420 --> 01:32:45.714
They got the Navy out there.
You gotta give up. You gotta stop.

1265
01:32:45.882 --> 01:32:47.633
I can't stop. Irish.

1266
01:32:47.801 --> 01:32:51.178
The Navy is not gonna let you win.
They can't let you win.

1267
01:32:52.055 --> 01:32:55.766
They would rather sink this boat
than let you get me back to Somalia.

1268
01:32:55.934 --> 01:32:56.976
It's over.

1269
01:33:00.647 --> 01:33:03.023
I come too far. Irish.

1270
01:33:03.608 --> 01:33:07.569
I can't give up. No.

1271
01:33:09.656 --> 01:33:11.657
[♪♪♪]

1272
01:33:27.674 --> 01:33:29.675
[PHONE RINGING]

1273
01:33:31.678 --> 01:33:32.720
Hello?

1274
01:33:32.887 --> 01:33:36.015
MAN:
The SEALs are inbound.
deploying three miles off our stern.

1275
01:33:36.182 --> 01:33:37.558
Roger that.

1276
01:33:38.560 --> 01:33:40.561
[WATER RUNNING]

1277
01:33:47.402 --> 01:33:48.986
[♪♪♪]

1278
01:34:02.876 --> 01:34:04.877
[GRUNTING]

1279
01:34:08.840 --> 01:34:16.138
[♪♪♪]

1280
01:34:49.297 --> 01:34:50.631
I need to piss.

1281
01:34:52.384 --> 01:34:54.093
Fast.

1282
01:35:20.286 --> 01:35:22.788
Saltwater would be good for your foot.

1283
01:35:24.416 --> 01:35:25.666
[YELLS]

1284
01:35:26.918 --> 01:35:28.377
MUSE [IN SOMALI]:
He got out!

1285
01:35:28.545 --> 01:35:31.171
Turn the boat around!

1286
01:35:31.339 --> 01:35:32.965
Bilal. you idiot!

1287
01:35:33.174 --> 01:35:35.175
[PIRATES SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

1288
01:35:36.636 --> 01:35:39.012
[♪♪♪]

1289
01:35:47.856 --> 01:35:49.898
MUSE:
Turn it! Faster. faster!

1290
01:35:52.444 --> 01:35:55.529
Move. or we'll leave you!

1291
01:35:56.448 --> 01:35:57.739
MAN 1:
Captain's in Combat.

1292
01:35:57.907 --> 01:36:00.409
MAN 2:
Cap. We got two in the water.
Two in the water.

1293
01:36:00.618 --> 01:36:03.078
WOMAN:
Starboard side. I see them both.

1294
01:36:03.580 --> 01:36:04.746
Two guys in the water.

1295
01:36:04.956 --> 01:36:07.958
CASTELLANO: Is one of them Phillips?
MAN 3: We don't know. We can't tell.

1296
01:36:08.126 --> 01:36:10.461
MAN 4:
They're in the water. In the water.

1297
01:36:10.670 --> 01:36:13.839
One may be Phillips
and probably one pirate. We don't know.

1298
01:36:14.007 --> 01:36:15.340
CASTELLANO:
We've gotta be sure.

1299
01:36:15.508 --> 01:36:17.134
Let's get a flare in the air.

1300
01:36:18.678 --> 01:36:21.180
Find him. Don't kill him.

1301
01:36:30.940 --> 01:36:32.524
[MUSE SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

1302
01:36:37.113 --> 01:36:39.490
MUSE:
Don't shoot!

1303
01:36:39.657 --> 01:36:41.742
NAJEE [IN ENGLISH]:
I'll shoot you!

1304
01:36:43.495 --> 01:36:45.287
Stop! What are you doing?

1305
01:36:45.455 --> 01:36:48.207
NAJEE [IN SOMALI]:
He's getting away!

1306
01:36:51.127 --> 01:36:54.630
Don't kill him!
Better to kill him than let him escape!

1307
01:36:57.091 --> 01:36:58.300
[GASPS]

1308
01:36:58.510 --> 01:37:00.761
MUSE:
There he is!

1309
01:37:03.848 --> 01:37:06.475
I'm ordering you. Don't kill him.

1310
01:37:08.061 --> 01:37:11.480
MAN 1 [OVER RADIO]:
Bainbridge. this is RHIB 3.
We have SEALs inbound.

1311
01:37:12.315 --> 01:37:17.069
Flare's up. captain.
Target angle 020
on the lifeboat right now.

1312
01:37:18.696 --> 01:37:20.322
CASTELLANO:
Can't tell who's in the water.

1313
01:37:20.490 --> 01:37:22.074
No clear shot at the Tangos.

1314
01:37:22.242 --> 01:37:24.785
Nobody shoots
unless there's a clear shot.

1315
01:37:24.994 --> 01:37:26.370
MUSE:
Where is he?

1316
01:37:30.291 --> 01:37:31.333
[GASPS]

1317
01:37:32.460 --> 01:37:34.461
Here he is! Here he is!

1318
01:37:37.382 --> 01:37:39.383
[MUFFLED SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

1319
01:37:39.759 --> 01:37:41.760
[PIRATES SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

1320
01:37:46.307 --> 01:37:47.724
MUSE:
He's here!

1321
01:37:51.938 --> 01:37:55.524
MAN:
One more in the water.
We've got one more in the water.

1322
01:37:55.692 --> 01:37:57.317
PHILLIPS:
Help!

1323
01:38:04.659 --> 01:38:05.701
Help!

1324
01:38:12.041 --> 01:38:13.375
[GUNFIRE]

1325
01:38:13.543 --> 01:38:15.544
[SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

1326
01:38:15.712 --> 01:38:17.045
PHILLIPS:
All right!

1327
01:38:17.255 --> 01:38:19.381
NAJEE [IN ENGLISH]: Come!
PHILLIPS: All right!

1328
01:38:19.549 --> 01:38:21.216
Come! Forward!
PHILLIPS: All right!

1329
01:38:21.384 --> 01:38:23.385
MUSE [IN ENGLISH]:
Got him.

1330
01:38:23.553 --> 01:38:24.970
NAJEE:
Come!

1331
01:38:25.138 --> 01:38:27.598
PHILLIPS:
Okay. okay.

1332
01:38:29.559 --> 01:38:32.477
Go in. Irish! Go! Go. Irish!

1333
01:38:33.396 --> 01:38:36.106
MAN 1:
Sir. the SEALs are coming aboard.

1334
01:38:36.941 --> 01:38:38.817
MAN 2 [OVER RADIO]:
Prepare to board the SEALs.

1335
01:38:45.783 --> 01:38:47.784
[PIRATES SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

1336
01:38:54.167 --> 01:38:56.335
Where are you go? Tell me! Tell me!

1337
01:38:56.502 --> 01:38:58.086
Are you crazy?

1338
01:39:01.466 --> 01:39:04.843
Where's the captain?
Waiting for you on the bridge. sir.

1339
01:39:07.221 --> 01:39:10.557
[NAJEE SHOUTING IN SOMALI
AND PHILLIPS GRUNTING]

1340
01:39:12.560 --> 01:39:14.102
NAJEE:
Not today!

1341
01:39:14.270 --> 01:39:15.520
Stop him!

1342
01:39:20.652 --> 01:39:22.736
[IN SOMALI]
That's enough!

1343
01:39:27.158 --> 01:39:28.992
MUSE:
Don't kill him!

1344
01:39:31.329 --> 01:39:33.330
If you kill him. we'll all die!

1345
01:39:35.291 --> 01:39:38.877
What do you want me to do with him?
What is he doing?

1346
01:39:39.087 --> 01:39:40.128
[ARGUING IN SOMALI]

1347
01:39:40.296 --> 01:39:42.964
[AIRCRAFT WHIRRING]

1348
01:39:43.758 --> 01:39:45.759
[♪♪♪]

1349
01:39:48.262 --> 01:39:50.889
Bainbridge to lifeboat.
you must surrender.

1350
01:39:51.057 --> 01:39:53.183
[OVER RADIO]
You will not be permitted to go further.

1351
01:39:53.351 --> 01:39:55.185
It's a helicopter!

1352
01:39:55.353 --> 01:39:57.521
MUSE:
Get to the other side!

1353
01:39:58.898 --> 01:40:00.857
[PIRATES SHOUTING IN SOMALI]

1354
01:40:01.818 --> 01:40:04.069
CASTELLANO:
Alabama lifeboat. respond.

1355
01:40:04.237 --> 01:40:05.737
Hurry! Go!

1356
01:40:05.905 --> 01:40:06.988
I'm trying.

1357
01:40:11.661 --> 01:40:12.828
Go!

1358
01:40:12.995 --> 01:40:16.957
CASTELLANO: You have a choice
to make. captain. Surrender now
and this ends peacefully.

1359
01:40:17.125 --> 01:40:19.793
Beyond that. I cannot help you.
You must surrender.

1360
01:40:19.961 --> 01:40:22.546
[IN SOMALI]
They think you are playing games.

1361
01:40:22.714 --> 01:40:24.798
Do something!

1362
01:40:24.966 --> 01:40:26.383
You cannot win this.

1363
01:40:33.516 --> 01:40:35.308
CASTELLANO:
Make the right decision here.

1364
01:40:35.476 --> 01:40:38.353
You are running out of time.
Do you understand me?

1365
01:40:38.521 --> 01:40:40.856
Do you want to go
to an American prison?

1366
01:40:41.023 --> 01:40:42.691
CASTELLANO:
This is your last chance.

1367
01:40:42.859 --> 01:40:44.818
Is that what you want?

1368
01:40:45.570 --> 01:40:47.404
I know how to handle America.

1369
01:40:47.572 --> 01:40:49.448
Give me the pistol.

1370
01:40:50.575 --> 01:40:52.993
They think I'm playing games. huh?

1371
01:40:53.161 --> 01:40:54.202
[SPEAKING IN SOMALI]

1372
01:40:54.370 --> 01:40:55.620
MUSE [IN ENGLISH]:
Go!

1373
01:40:56.456 --> 01:40:58.248
Go!

1374
01:40:58.458 --> 01:41:00.333
Up ladder.

1375
01:41:03.379 --> 01:41:04.546
Make a hole.

1376
01:41:14.724 --> 01:41:17.267
MAN:
Target in the hatch.
This is Bainbridge out.

1377
01:41:17.977 --> 01:41:20.103
They're holding a gun
to Phillips' head.

1378
01:41:20.271 --> 01:41:23.690
He's kind of yelling
and waving his pistol back and forth.

1379
01:41:26.152 --> 01:41:30.363
I kill him! I kill him! Now! I kill him!

1380
01:41:33.451 --> 01:41:35.160
MAN 1:
We got shots fired. captain.

1381
01:41:35.328 --> 01:41:37.496
MAN 2: How many shots?
MAN 1: Who fired? Who fired?

1382
01:41:37.663 --> 01:41:39.623
We're losing this.

1383
01:41:48.674 --> 01:41:49.716
Now what?

1384
01:41:50.134 --> 01:41:51.343
NAJEE:
They have no respect for us.

1385
01:41:51.511 --> 01:41:54.054
We have to play games?

1386
01:41:58.267 --> 01:42:00.769
[IN SOMALI]
Give me the radio.

1387
01:42:01.854 --> 01:42:06.149
NAJEE:
The helicopter is coming back.

1388
01:42:08.945 --> 01:42:11.404
[IN ENGLISH]
America. I kill hostage now!

1389
01:42:11.572 --> 01:42:14.991
I kill hostage now!
I'm gonna put him in a body bag!

1390
01:42:15.159 --> 01:42:17.911
[SHOUTS IN SOMALI]

1391
01:42:24.585 --> 01:42:27.295
Talk. Talk.

1392
01:42:27.463 --> 01:42:32.759
They got a gun to my throat. and they're
gonna use a survival suit as a body bag.

1393
01:42:38.558 --> 01:42:44.521
You're not just a fisherman.

1394
01:42:48.317 --> 01:42:52.946
SEAL COMMANDER [OVER RADIO]:
Men of the Alabama lifeboat.
I'm here to talk about your money.

1395
01:42:54.115 --> 01:42:57.033
Repeat.
I'm here to discuss your money.

1396
01:43:02.540 --> 01:43:03.665
Who is this?

1397
01:43:03.833 --> 01:43:07.002
I'm the negotiator.
I'm authorized to negotiate with you.

1398
01:43:10.423 --> 01:43:11.631
Insurance man?

1399
01:43:11.799 --> 01:43:15.844
Now. you are Abduwali Muse. right?
From Jariban. Puntland?

1400
01:43:16.012 --> 01:43:18.972
From the clans of the Hawiye
and the Daarood?

1401
01:43:19.140 --> 01:43:20.807
Your friends are Adan Bilal

1402
01:43:21.017 --> 01:43:24.060
Walid Elmi and Nour Najee.

1403
01:43:24.228 --> 01:43:27.981
But you are Muse. You're in command.
Is that correct?

1404
01:43:28.190 --> 01:43:30.191
[♪♪♪]

1405
01:43:30.943 --> 01:43:32.193
They know us.

1406
01:43:32.361 --> 01:43:34.404
We spoke with the elders of your tribe.

1407
01:43:34.572 --> 01:43:38.408
They are coming here to negotiate
a deal. an exchange.

1408
01:43:38.618 --> 01:43:42.495
We get our man. you get your money.
But this has to be done in confidence.

1409
01:43:42.663 --> 01:43:46.166
We don't want anyone to see
the exchange. Neither do the elders.

1410
01:43:46.334 --> 01:43:47.459
It's a lie.

1411
01:43:47.627 --> 01:43:50.795
SEAL COMMANDER:
You're low on fuel.
We got some weather coming in.

1412
01:43:50.963 --> 01:43:55.300
so I'm suggesting that we tow you out
to the exchange point.

1413
01:43:55.468 --> 01:43:58.678
But we need someone to come aboard
and negotiate the deal.

1414
01:43:58.846 --> 01:44:00.263
It's an ambush.

1415
01:44:00.932 --> 01:44:02.933
SEAL COMMANDER:
Captain.

1416
01:44:12.944 --> 01:44:14.444
Okay.

1417
01:44:17.657 --> 01:44:19.532
It's an ambush.

1418
01:44:23.996 --> 01:44:25.997
[♪♪♪]

1419
01:44:43.432 --> 01:44:45.433
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

1420
01:44:48.938 --> 01:44:50.730
MAN 1:
Keep me posted on status.

1421
01:44:54.068 --> 01:44:57.278
MAN 2: Roger.
Comms test radio check.

1422
01:44:59.448 --> 01:45:04.619
OSS. TAO. I need eyes on the RHIB.
I need eyes on the RHIB.

1423
01:45:05.079 --> 01:45:06.705
Captain's in Combat.

1424
01:45:06.914 --> 01:45:10.166
CASTELLANO:
Tactical command
is now with the SEAL team.

1425
01:45:11.752 --> 01:45:13.086
SEAL COMMANDER:
TAO. where we at?

1426
01:45:13.295 --> 01:45:15.547
MAN:
RHIBs are headed inbound
to the lifeboat.

1427
01:45:15.715 --> 01:45:18.466
Halyburton and Boxer are standing by
for your orders.

1428
01:45:18.634 --> 01:45:22.053
ASTAC. TAO.
I need a status at Halyburton's helo.

1429
01:45:23.556 --> 01:45:25.557
[AIRCRAFT WHIRRING]

1430
01:45:26.976 --> 01:45:28.977
[♪♪♪]

1431
01:45:44.285 --> 01:45:46.786
MUSE [IN SOMALI]:
You need to be strong.

1432
01:45:46.954 --> 01:45:49.122
Don't let anyone in.

1433
01:45:56.839 --> 01:45:59.007
Whatever happens. don't stop.

1434
01:45:59.175 --> 01:46:00.717
ELMI:
It's my job.

1435
01:46:10.811 --> 01:46:12.187
[IN ENGLISH]
Everything good. Irish.

1436
01:46:13.731 --> 01:46:16.399
Everything gonna be okay.

1437
01:46:17.318 --> 01:46:19.360
I go Navy ship.

1438
01:46:20.821 --> 01:46:22.572
get dollars.

1439
01:46:24.116 --> 01:46:25.992
you go home.

1440
01:46:30.831 --> 01:46:32.999
It was supposed to be easy.

1441
01:46:34.835 --> 01:46:36.711
I take ship...

1442
01:46:38.506 --> 01:46:40.173
ransom...

1443
01:46:42.510 --> 01:46:44.344
nobody get hurt.

1444
01:46:44.512 --> 01:46:48.681
You had $30.000
and a way to Somalia.

1445
01:46:51.018 --> 01:46:52.477
It wasn't enough?

1446
01:46:55.189 --> 01:46:57.232
I got bosses.

1447
01:46:57.900 --> 01:46:59.776
They got rules.

1448
01:46:59.944 --> 01:47:02.278
We all got bosses.

1449
01:47:07.368 --> 01:47:10.370
There's gotta be something
other than being a fisherman

1450
01:47:10.538 --> 01:47:12.330
and kidnapping people.

1451
01:47:15.417 --> 01:47:17.669
Maybe in America. Irish.

1452
